title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: dakota dirt cake
directions: Place half of the crushed cookies in the bottom of a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan, covering the bottom completely.
Blend the cream cheese and margarine until smooth, then fold in the nondairy whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Use a low speed, if necessary.

title: milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Serve immediately.

title: skillet turkey dinner
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Stir in flour and basil and cook for a couple of minutes.
Stir in milk slowly.
Add turkey, tamari and parsley and simmer until thick.
Serve over rice, noodles or bread.
Serves 2.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a chilled, unbaked pastry shell.
Bake until firm at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon thyme sauce
directions: Blend.
Whip the cottage cheese.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Serve with fish or vegetables or baked potatoes.
Add 2 tablespoons more skim milk.
Serve as a dressing.

title: sand and cornstarch modeling dough
directions: Mix sand and cornstarch.
Add hot water and stir vigorously. Add food coloring if desired.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Beat Cool Whip, oleo and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add pineapple, peanuts and apples. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine bananas, orange juice, lemonade and sugar in blender. Blend until smooth.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a large container. Freeze overnight, stirring once.
Let thaw to slushy stage and serve.
Serves 23 (6 ounce) cups.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as instructed on the box, then add bananas and nuts.
Bake as instructed on the cake mix.
Let cool completely. (Makes 3 layers.)
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat; brown meat.
Stir in onion soup mix and mushrooms with liquid; heat until bubbling.
Slowly stir in sour cream until thoroughly blended.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated thoroughly.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Grease loaf tin, have a beer, turn oven on to 350°, have a beer.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, have a beer.
Beat egg and orange juice in bowl, have a beer.
Mix frozen berries in flour mixture, quickly add orange juice and egg mixture.
Put in tin and bake 1 hour at 350° or when toothpick comes out not sticky.

title: garlic pasta toss
directions: Cook pasta as per packet directions; drain.
In small skillet, cook garlic in oil until golden.
Add water and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
In large bowl, toss hot angel hair with garlic mixture and parsley.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Add meal with water.
Put layer of corn bread mixture, then layer of cheese, until the skillet is full.
Bake in greased 9-inch skillet at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat and cook chicken, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until almost done. Stir in onion, carrots and celery. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes. Stir in savory herb with garlic soup mix, blended with milk. Bring to the boiling point over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Cook 1 minute. Turn into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Arrange biscuits on top of chicken mixture with edges touching. Bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: blueberries in snow
directions: Combine cool whip and cream cheese until smooth; cover bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish with mixture. Tear angel food cake into pieces and press in pan over mixture. Pour can of pie filling over cake; top with remaining cream cheese mixture.

title: herb baked potato
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until celery is tender. Take potato and make several slices large enough to spoon in mixture in each slice.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, dates and eggs to a soft boil.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts, if desired.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place in refrigerator for awhile.
Slice and they are ready to serve.

title: pizza carbonara
directions: Unroll pizza crust. Press onto a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Build up edges slightly. Prick dough thoroughly with a fork. Bake at 425° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together next 4 ingredients and pour over top of Tater Tots.
Top with corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over top of corn flakes and bake (uncovered) at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Make white sauce:
Combine margarine, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 macaroni in dish, 1/2 cheese, then 1/2 white sauce.
Repeat.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 15 minutes more at 375°.

title: spaghetti sauce for rigatoni
directions: Take casing off sausage or buy uncased and fry with cubed butter and cubed margarine; add onion and garlic.
Fry until soft, not browned.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 3 or 4 hours.
This sauce should be enough for 3 or 4 pounds rigatoni.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Heat for 30 seconds. Spread in generously greased square pan.
Sprinkle with crumble mixture of remaining 4 ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: date and nut tiffin loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix with fingers until well coated.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla and blend with fingers.
Mix in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Brush loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) with butter; flour lightly and add batter, smoothing it with your hands.
Cover top of pan with foil, folding around the edge of pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove foil and increase heat to 325°.
Let remain in oven 10 to 15 minutes longer or until top becomes faintly brown.
Remove from oven and let set 5 minutes.
Loosen with dull knife.
Turn upside down on cake rack.
When cool, wrap and store or freeze.
Slice thinly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: The night before, using a blender or food chopper, grind cranberries, then mix with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and refrigerate. Add remaining ingredients the next day. Add Cool Whip just before serving. Serves 20.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 3 minutes or until plump.
Let cool.
Mix all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Then add raisins.
Add dry ingredients to the wet mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: vegetable cheese dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli, saute celery and onion in butter. Add broccoli, soup, cheese and seasonings.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Prepare taco mix according to directions.
Cut up lettuce and tomatoes and mix together.
Add hamburger, chips and cheese just before you serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients; serve chilled.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel, cut up and boil potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain and mash with electric mixer, adding 1 stick butter.
Put into a buttered casserole.
Pour syrup on top and cut into potatoes with knife.
Top with 1/2 stick of butter, cut into pats. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes start to brown around the sides.
My family's favorite!

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; drain mushrooms.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Can be frozen.

title: hungarian double decker pastry
directions: Mix walnuts and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken or turkey on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mixed vegetables.
In a bowl, mix broth and soup.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: white mts. muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Melt the butter.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir well.
Grease muffin tin and fill half full.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: homestyle tuna pot pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling into pie pan.
Top with second crust.
Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top of crust to vent and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Bake time: 45 to 50 minutes.

title: "crabby l. d."
directions: Mix all well.
Add Russian dressing to taste and put in fridge.
Great with crackers or French bread.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together
flour,
sugar
and
salt
in large bowl. Bring to a
boil the oil, water and cocoa; pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla together; add to mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Add flavoring, then pecans. Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured, at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples. Peel off collar around the top.
Place in a baking dish.
Put remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Apples will be soft but not mushy.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil the potatoes until mushy.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer real good.
Pour into 2 deep dishes.

title: hungarian stew with noodles
directions: Heat oil in a large Dutch oven; add garlic and cook 1 minute over medium-high heat.
Discard garlic.
Add beef and onions; cook until the meat is browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomato paste, water, paprika, salt, pepper and bay leaf; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat 2 hours or until meat is tender; stir occasionally.
Toss noodles with butter and parsley.
Top stew with lemon rind and caraway seed; serve with egg noodles.

title: chicken breasts dijon
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap and pound slightly flat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon each oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for approximately 4 minutes on each side. Do not overcook or they will be dry. Transfer to warm serving platter. Add chives or green onion and parsley to pan.
Cook for 15 seconds. Whisk in mustard and broth. Cook for 15 seconds longer.
Stir briskly.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.
Good with noodles with tomato sauce, steamed broccoli and a fresh salad.

title: ham-asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cut ham slices into 2 pieces.
Cut asparagus into same size. Spread cream cheese on ham.
Lay asparagus in center and roll up. Put toothpick through them.
Very attractive and tasty.

title: chicken pot pie or turkey
directions: Prepare pastry; set aside.
Cook peas and carrots according to package directions.
Drain.
In a saucepan, cook onions and mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, spices and pepper.
Add broth and milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in peas and carrots, chicken, parsley and pimiento; heat until bubbly.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll pastry into a 13 x 9-inch rectangle.
Place over chicken mixture, flute edges and cut slits in top.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings (633 calories and 37 grams fat).

title: fat free dip
directions: Blend together with blender for 20 to 30 seconds.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Drain pineapple; add flour, sugar and cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble crackers over the top of mixture.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good with meat dishes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix marinade.
Place roast in dish with marinade.
Pierce meat with fork and turn often.
Marinate at least 4 hours.
Best to marinate overnight.

title: fix and forget casserole
directions: Carefully layer all ingredients in the order listed in a baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, cut the cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
In another bowl, mix together all the other ingredients.
Pour over cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Tastes better the next day.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Nuts optional).
Grease 8 inch tin.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and pepper in frying pan.
Cook until brown.
Mix all other ingredients in pot, then add mixture and simmer for 1 hour.
Add flour, if needed, for thickness.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In large bowl beat sugar, margarine, molasses and eggs until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg; mix well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cookies will puff up and flatten during baking.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.

title: potato or macaroni salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Enough for 6 to 8 large potatoes.
For macaroni use about 2 cups.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: Grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups.
In a large mixing bowl stir together flour, pudding mix, chocolate pieces, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl combine beaten eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture, just until combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting, sprinkle with green sugar then milk chocolate pieces.
Makes 18.

title: crusty topped cauliflower
directions: Cook
cauliflower
whole in small amount of water about 20 minutes.
Drain carefully.	Place cauliflower in flat pan. Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over cooked cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: nana's lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly, spooning off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles according to directions on package; drain and rinse in cold water.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: deviled crab balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in butter until soft. Cut crusts from bread; crumble bread into small bits in a large bowl.
Add eggs, salt and mustard; mix well.
Stir in onion, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Gently fold in crabmeat; shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with mustard sauce.
Makes about 40 balls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and place in casserole and dot with butter, then bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion and celery. Add other ingredients and simmer until done (1 hour).

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add cheese, salt and onion and mix.
Stir in eggs and mix.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Dot with margarine, paprika and green pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May top with 2 cups herb seasoned bread crumbs before adding margarine, paprika and green pepper.

title: chocolate chip and sour cream brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix butter and brown sugar until blended.
Add egg, sour cream and vanilla; beat until light.
Add cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend in flour until well mixed.
Add chocolate chips, then spread batter evenly into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
To test, make sure center springs back when touching.
Cool in pan.
Top with sifted powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: seven minute frosting(marshmallow frosting)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except vanilla. Beat in double boiler (or bowl placed in pan of hot water) with electric mixer, until mixture stands in soft peaks (7 to 10 minutes). Remove from heat; add vanilla. Beat until very thick. Enough frosting for a two layer cake.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon juice, apples and sugar. Place apples in greased Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice and sugar.
Put mixture over top of apples and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Place alternate layers of drained noodles, ham and 1/2 of cheese in a baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, mushrooms and seasonings.
Pour over noodles and ham.
Top with the rest of the cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat eggs and
sugar until light colored.
Add 1 cup vegetable oil. Beat until
blended.
In
a separate bowl sift flour, cinnamon, baking
powder,
salt
and soda.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and
beat 2 minutes. Stir in crushed pineapple, well drained,
and walnuts, vanilla and zucchini (zucchini squeezed in paper
towel).
Mix
thoroughly. Pour batter into well-greased
and
floured
10-inch tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour fluted tube or 10-inch tube pan.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside. In large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour 1/2 batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mix.
Cover with remaining batter.

title: the best cranberry mold ever
directions: Dissolve jello in water, cool until slightly thickened.
Grind cranberries, orange, apples and nuts.
Add sugar and salt, blend thoroughly.
Add to jello and place in a 2-quart ring mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with endive, watercress or lettuce. Place small bowl of whipped cream salad dressing in center of mold.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: overnight ham-and-cheese bake
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Place bread, buttered side down, in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Place ham on top of cheese, then add mushrooms and chiles.
Top with Jack cheese.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt, paprika, basil, onion salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, milk and butter over low heat.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour
1/2 of batter into 9 x 11-inch greased cake pan. Bake for
15 minutes at 325°.
Pour caramel mixture over cake and then
sprinkle
with
nuts and chocolate chips. Pour rest of batter
over
cake
topping
and
bake another 15 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and spread on cool crust.

title: hot spice percolator punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, water and cranberry juice in bottom part of an 8-cup electric percolator, and the rest of the ingredients in the basket on top.
Perk for 10 minutes or until the spices permeate.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients
and place in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice quiche
directions: Combine
rice, half of cheese, 1 egg (slightly beaten), salt and
pepper.
Mix
together
and
press firmly in an even layer on bottom
of
9-inch
pie pan (or quiche pan).
Beat 2 eggs slightly.
Stir in broccoli, milk and mushrooms.
Season with salt and
pepper.
Spoon over rice mixture in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes
at
Remove
from
oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook grits 10 minutes.
Cook onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon butter for a few minutes; push to side of skillet. Grate zucchini; add rice, cooked corn grits, two eggs and seasonings.
Mix and add to onion-pepper in skillet.
You can cook on stove top slowly on low heat, turning often.
Or bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese over top; return to oven to melt.
Serves 4.
Enjoy!

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, brown sugar and honey.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: quick pizzas
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet until brown.
Meanwhile, roll biscuits into 4-inch rounds.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Top each with meat, then with slice of Mozzarella (or sharp cheese) and a little chili sauce, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake at 550° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Watch carefully; they can burn pretty quick.

title: preacher cobbler
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Add sugar and flour.
Blend until crumbly. Layer fruit in a 13 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add crumbs evenly over fruit.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown. Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: dee's party mix
directions: Mix all cereals and nuts together.
Pour the canola Oil on top.
Mix the 1 cup margarine with the spices and pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 200 degrees for one hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: family pie
directions: Mix
flour, sugar and milk.
Place fresh fruit in glass baking dish.
Pour
batter over top of fruit and cut up butter and dot around on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Divide 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of the grapes into small clusters of all colors.
Fill a ring mold with the clusters; barely cover with water and freeze until solid.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to temperature called for on crescent roll package.
Separate dough into triangular sections.
Arrange triangles of dough, side by side, in a circle in a 14-inch round pizza pan.
Press the edges of dough together with your fingers to make one large circle of dough.
Flute edges and prick bottom with a fork.
Bake for time called for on package.

title: pizza squares
directions: Unroll can of rolls on large cookie sheet.
Press like pizza crust dough.
Bake it at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 4 ingredients until smooth (cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing).
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with veggies and cheese.
Cut in squares.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine and cook butter, sugar and milk, stirring constantly to soft ball stage.
Put chocolate chips and marshmallows into large bowl.
Toss together gently and add mixture, then nuts. Beat until smooth, then add vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: homos with tahini
directions: Cook chickpeas in saucepan for about 5 minutes.
Press through food mill or sieve into a bowl.
Crush garlic with salt; add tahini and lemon juice; mix well.
Blend together with chickpeas and season to taste.
Thin with cold water to desired consistency. Garnish with oil and parsley if desired.
Serve with pita bread as an appetizer.

title: snickers pie
directions: Place Snickers in microwave-safe bowl.	Microwave on medium-high until melted.
Sir candy bars until smooth.
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip and stir until mixed well.
Pour mixture into pie shell and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Remove pie from refrigerator and spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Put 1 package rolls into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Put in pan and cover with second package of crescent rolls.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Rinse the turkey well and pat dry inside and out.
Using a shaker, sprinkle inside and out with salt and then shake on cayenne pepper, making sure to rub the seasonings into the meat.
Wash your hands!

Pour enough peanut oil into a large 40-quart pot to insure that the turkey will be covered when fully lowered into the pot. Make sure the pot is large enough that the oil won't overflow. Heat oil to 350° to 375°, then holding onto the legs, very slowly lower the bird all the way into the oil.
Fry about 3 to 4 minutes per pound.
Some tongs or a long fork makes handling much easier. Test for doneness at the bone at the thigh joint.
Carefully remove the turkey from oil, allowing it to drain.
Carve as usual.

title: mel's red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, beating well after each. In a separate large bowl, sift together cake flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.

Add food coloring to mixture of sugar, oil and eggs. Alternately add buttermilk and flour, starting with buttermilk and ending with flour. Add vanilla and vinegar. Beat until well-mixed. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on racks.

title: pa dendy's delight
directions: Bring to boil in frypan and add 1 cup cornmeal (self-rising) or 1 cup cracker meal.
Cook and stir until thick, then slightly cool and eat.

title: english toffee(holiday favorite!)
directions: In a large iron skillet, combine water, butter and sugar. Cook on high heat, stirring constantly.
Cook candy to a light brown color (candy will bubble and leave the side of the pan). Cook a little longer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour out on a baking sheet covered with buttered foil.
When candy starts to cool, turn over so it does not stick.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over candy while hot.
Yields 1/2 pound candy.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs and gradually add the sugar.
Beating at a high speed, add the flour.
Reduce the speed a bit and add the condensed milk and the evaporated milk.
Add only enough homogenized milk to fill a 1-gallon container.
Freeze.

title: "clergy in a hurry" spaghetti
directions: Fill large pot with water; when boiling dump in spaghetti. Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Test for doneness by throwing one noodle against the wall.
If it sticks, it's done. During a break from stirring, dump sauce into another pan.
Cook it until hot.
Drain water from noodles.
Serve by dumping sauce on top of spaghetti.
This recipe is especially tasty when served with Lyncourt Bakery bread and vanilla ice cream.

title: hootch
directions: Mix beer, Southern Comfort, vodka, sloe gin and orange juice in a 64 ounce pitcher.
Fill to top of pitcher with ice.
Add Squirt and 7-Up.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in heavy pan.
Boil over medium heat for 7 minutes. Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add last two ingredients.
Beat until stiff.

title: jiggler bells
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl, stirring 3 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Do not add cold water. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° until egg is done and the casserole is slightly brown on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and baking soda. Mix well.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch dish until firm.
Heat pineapple juice in double boiler.
Add flour and sugar to beaten egg.
Mix with juice and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin.
Shred Cheddar cheese generously over all.
Nuts may be added.

title: baked french toast
directions: Crush corn flakes to measure 1 cup crumbs.
Place in shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Cook frozen onion until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce, ending with a sauce layer. Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Makes 5 servings.

title: shrimp diane
directions: In a large skillet melt 1 stick of butter over high heat. When almost melted, add green onions, salt, garlic, peppers, basil, thyme and oregano.
Stir well.
Add shrimp and saute until pink (1 minute), shaking pan back and froth.
Add mushrooms and 1/4 cup of stock.
Then add 4 tablespoons butter in chunks and continue cooking and shaking.
Before butter melts, add parsley and 2 tablespoons stock and continue cooking and shaking until mixed and sauce is consistency of cream.
Serve over rice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine margarine, hamburger, flour, green peppers and onion. Cook until brown,.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions, green peppers and red peppers.
Add salt.
Cover with boiling water and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain very well.
Rinse and drain very well again. Prepare the following and bring to a boil:
sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Add drained vegetables and boil 15 minutes.
Make a paste of 3 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Add to hot relish and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Pour into jars while hot.

title: tender roast beef
directions: Put meat fat side down in roasting pan.
Add enough water to pan to cover meat 3/4 way up.
Salt top of meat (meat is frozen). Do not cover pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Turn meat over. Cut off fat and discard.
Sprinkle top of meat with pepper, Season-All and paprika.
Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut onions in half and place in pan next to meat.
Sprinkle onions with soy sauce.
Decrease temperature to 350° and bake 1 hour.
Cover meat with au jus mix.
Add Washington seasoning to water in pan. Cover pan with lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ephiphany cake
directions: Make cake and bake with items inside.

title: appetizer chicken roll up
directions: Cut chicken into approximately 1 inch cubes.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap chicken cubes with 1/2 strip of bacon. Secure with tooth pick.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain well.
Cover with soy sauce.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together and lay out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: english pea-asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° until it starts to bubble.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread chicken pieces evenly over bottom of dish.
In a bowl, mix together broth, soup and vegetables.
Pour on top of chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk together; pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters and liquid about 5 minutes until edges curl.
Stir into hot milk.
Add butter and season to taste.

title: feed 'em all cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package and bake in a large 17 inch x 11 inch x 2 1/4 inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool.
Cream cream cheese.
Add pudding mix and milk. Blend on low speed for 2 minutes.
Pudding will thicken as it rests.
Spread on cake after it thickens.
Layer with pineapple, then layer bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas and top with coconut.
Serves 20.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add processed cheese.
Stir in soups, beans and tomatoes and green chilies until well mixed and cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch dish, layer meat mixture with tortilla chips, beginning with meat mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cocoalight cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.	Add eggs one at a time,
beating after each.	Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.	Bake in three greased 8-inch layer pans at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together; add beaten eggs.
Add peanut butter, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and oatmeal.
Mix well into other ingredients.
Add M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: In small bowl, combine milk and chocolate syrup; set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold in chocolate mixture, marshmallows, chocolate chip, and nuts. Transfer to a freezer proof container.
Cover and freeze for 5 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
You do not need an ice cream freezer for this recipe. Yield: 1 1/2 quarts.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Beat eggs and add milk and salt to dry ingredients.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken, remove and chill.
Add vanilla and cream, then freeze in freezer.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour peaches with juice over batter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add a few pats of butter on top.
Bake at 325° until batter is firm.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, onion and chillies.
Dip tortillas in warmed broth.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: quick gravy
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Return to skillet.
Add soup and water or milk.
Cook on low to medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Serve over bread, toast, pasta or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: In large bowl with fork, stir together dry ingredients.
In small bowl, beat together milk, peanut butter, oil and egg.
Stir into flour mixture until moistened.
Line muffin pans and spray with Mazola no-stick.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean and tops are lightly browned.

title: seafood lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.
Thoroughly combine filling ingredients with forks (crab delights, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg, parsley flakes and onion powder).
Spread 1/3 filling on each noodle.
Roll tightly; place seam-side down in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Pour sauce over roll-ups.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.

Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, egg whites, onion, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in a large bowl; mix until blended and fold in macaroni. Spoon mixture into a 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°) for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: creme fudge
directions: Stir till creamy- Pour in buttered pan.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done. Remove from pot and let broth cool. Skim off excess fat from broth. Remove chicken from bone and place in bowl. Crumble crackers over chicken. Pour broth over chicken and crackers. Mix until very moist, but not soupy. Pour into a sprayed 9 x 13 baking dish and bake at 350° until top is golden brown and pulling away from sides of dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in lemon juice and butter; stir in lemon rind.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix
all
together
(except
zucchini).
Add
zucchini. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or light brown on the top.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef; add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Stir in soup and place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle peas and carrots over first ingredients.
Arrange mashed potatoes in a ring on top, allowing filling to show through. Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Add garlic and soups.
Mix well.
Fold in cooked macaroni.
Pour in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gauffrette (french cookies)
directions: With butter at room temperature, cut in sugar.
Add beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add flour until mixture can be handled easily.
Roll into small pieces.
Cook in cookie iron on top of stove.
Turn as needed.
Makes 14 to 20 dozen cookies.
Keeps well.
Is especially good at Christmastime.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Slice cookie dough and spread a layer of slices on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over the cookie dough.
Cover the filling with the remaining slices of cookie dough.
Sprinkle nuts over top; bake in a 300° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Saute 10 minutes until soft.
Transfer to saucepan.
Add tomatoes and rest of seasoning.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Stir together all ingredients (except bacon) and put in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Top beans with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef-stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Immerse cabbage into boiling water until bright green.
For the filling, brown the ground beef and onion, then drain.
Combine meat with rice, butter, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and sage.
Put filling near base of each leaf and roll up, folding edges under. Place cabbage rolls in rows in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (45 minutes if refrigerated).
Serve with Tomato Sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn bread dressing(for fowl)
directions: Scald your biscuits with the broth.
Add mashed corn bread and potatoes.
Add the egg, salt and pepper.
Mix with enough broth to be able to stir with a spoon (hush puppy consistency, not drippy). Add the giblets and put in a well-greased baking dish.
Brush some grease from the broth on top.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix together prepared Kool-Aid and lemonade.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Spoon sherbet into mixture.
Pour 7-Up over. Serve.
Serves 25-30.

title: hermits
directions: Spoon on Tbsp. size of batter to cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake chunks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Stir in crumbs and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press to cover bottom of pan.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, cocoa, egg and vanilla at medium speed until smooth.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake 20 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain on paper towel.
Melt 1/2 stick butter with cheese.
Melt another 3/4 stick butter and add cracker crumbs.
In baking dish, put broccoli, then cheese.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 375° until heated through and crackers are brown.

title: tacoed eggs
directions: In bowl, combine eggs, cheese, onion, green pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir in skillet until eggs are almost set. Add taco meat.
Cook until eggs set.
Spoon onto warmed tortilla and roll up.
Top with salsa, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put hamburg in bottom of baking pan.
Add mixed vegetables and soup.
Add cheese on top, then top with Tater Tots in rows.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Crumb flour, sugar and Crisco together with pastry blender. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add molasses, water and baking soda.
Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch greased, floured baking dish. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan.
In bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed.
Hand mix only.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Comes out very moist.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until smooth; whip eggs and add, then add mashed bananas.
Add sifted flour, salt and soda.
Fold into mixture and add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Preheat oven at 325° (glass pan) or 350° (tin pan).
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lasagna (delicious!)
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat. Add the next 8 ingredients. Simmer at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in boiling, salted water about 15 minutes. Drain; rinse in cold water. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 1 tsp. salt, pepper, parsley flakes, and Parmesan cheese (separately from meat). Using 13x9x2 pan, place small amount of meat mixture in bottom of pan; then 4 noodles; then spread half of cottage cheese mixture; then half of Mozzarella cheese; then half of meat sauce. Repeat the layers. Bake in moderate oven (350°-375°) about 45-50 minutes. Let stand about 15 minutes before cutting into serving pieces. This may be divided in two pans for smaller meals. Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything, except stuffing mix, and put into casserole dish.
Cover with dry stuffing mix straight from the bag.
(I use about 4 ounces.)
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix well the cooking wine, egg, soy sauce, white pepper and curry powder.
Marinate chicken 3 or 4
hours or refrigerate overnight.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate, apples and vanilla until evenly distributed.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: sugar-free graham cracker cake
directions: Prepare pudding by instructions on box.
In a glass loaf pan, put a layer of graham crackers, then a layer of pudding and layer until pudding is gone.
Top with Cool Whip and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Um-um good.

title: anise cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a tube pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hunters' chicken
directions: In large frypan, heat oil and brown chicken.
Remove chicken; saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil.
Put chicken back and add remaining ingredients except butter and parsley.
Cook covered over low heat until tender, about 35 minutes.
Arrange on platter. Add butter and parsley to sauce and pour over chicken.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla. Pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: spinach party dip
directions: Mix all well and refrigerate overnight.

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add any other ingredients you wish after baking, such as banana chips, raisins, various nuts, apple chips, etc.

title: orange fruit dip
directions: Mix orange juice and milk.
Beat in pudding mix on low speed and beat for 2 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with fruit to dip.
Strawberries, bananas and pineapple chunks are especially good.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast.
Add eggs, then flour.
Mix to smooth, soft dough. Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place dough in greased bowl, cover and let rise until at least doubled in bulk.
Divide dough in thirds.
Roll each third on lightly floured surface to 9-inch circle.
Cut each circle in 12 to 16 wedge-shaped pieces.
Roll each wedge, starting with wide end and rolling to point.
Arrange in greased baking pan and brush with melted butter or margarine. Cover and let rise until very light.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
For crescents, shape in curve on baking pan.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 1 hour in covered casserole at 325°.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Reduce heat; add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes with onions until tender.
Pour off some of liquid, then add carrots, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook until sort of thick.
Add about 1 cup of milk and cook a little more. Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Top with chicken, then combine mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Pour over chicken; cover all with thin layer of mayonnaise.
Top with diced cheese.
Blend milk, eggs and salt; pour over cheese.
Mix soups and pimentos; spoon over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a blender or by hand.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. The flour will settle to form a crust.
The coconut forms a topping.
The center is an egg custard pumpkin filling. Delicious!

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: gelatin delight
directions: Mix lime jello with cottage cheese until jello dissolves.
Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add nuts if desired.

title: fresh fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water and cool.
Extract juice from fruit.
Add cooled sugar syrup to juices and add cold water and ice, if available.
Serve cold.
Yield:
4 gallons or 50 (10-ounce) servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: arroz rojo(red rice)
directions: Rinse rice.
Mash garlic with salt to make a paste.
Heat oil in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Add rice; cook and stir over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add onion and garlic paste; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer until most of the liquid has been absorbed.
Reduce heat to very low; steam for 30 to 45 minutes, until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, dry mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle over corn.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In large
saucepan,
add
cheese
to
milk.
Stir
over medium heat until cheese is completely melted.
When cheese is smooth, it is ready to pour over macaroni or vegetables.

title: jewel's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
(Do not add eggs one at a time and do not beat eggs before adding to mix.) Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and mix well. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper turkey skillet
directions: Slice turkey into 1/8-inch thick pieces.
In a small bowl combine broth, soy sauce and sweetener.
In a large skillet, heat to medium and add one tablespoon oil.
Add half turkey and stir-fry 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove turkey; add rest of oil and turkey. Stir-fry until lightly browned.
Remove turkey.
Add vegetables to same skillet, stirring occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir sauce mixture into the vegetables, stirring until combined.
Add turkey and cook until tender.
In a glass measuring cup, combine water and cornstarch.
Stir into turkey mixture and bring to a boil. Contains approximately 275 calories.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix meal, boiling water and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat a skillet over medium-high flame.
Oil it well. Fry small cakes until browned, then turn to cook other side. Makes 12 johnnycakes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stone soup
directions: Heat water in a large pot.
Add the stone.
Add rice, carrots, potatoes, celery and onions.
Boil until these ingredients are soft.
Add tomatoes, corn, peas, bouillon and salt.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove stone.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes and onions until tender in liquid from peas.
Drain off liquid and add oil from tuna and enough milk to make 2 cups of liquid.
Melt butter, blend in flour, and add liquid stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over cooked vegetables.
Add tuna and peas.
Season to taste.
Turn into greased casserole dish and cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add to milk mixture. Add milk and yeast to flour.
Mix well.
Let set until it rises. Roll and cut into biscuits.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix milk, flour and melted oleo and put in the bottom of a big shallow baking dish.
Mix chicken, eggs, broth and soup and pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown, at least 1 hour.

title: party wieners
directions: Wrap wieners in bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Pour brown sugar
over
the
wieners in a crock-pot and cook on low for 2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat sugar, pineapple and Jell-O together, dissolving Jell-O. Mix all ingredients together. Chill in refrigerator until it sets good or overnight.

title: banana cream layer cake
directions: Sift together 3 times the dry ingredients.
Add water and lemon rind to egg yolks.
Beat until tripled in volume.
Add 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time, beating slowly with the beater.
Beat whites until foamy.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until soft peaks.
Fold into the flour mixture.
Pour into 2 ungreased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream and bananas on top.
Slice bananas and put layer between cake layers.

title: mexicali bean and bacon dip
directions: Place bacon in 1 1/2 qt. Microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with paper towels and microwave on high 3 to 4 minutes, or until crisp; stirring halfway through cooking time.
Drain off and discard bacon fat.
Add beans to bacon; mash with fork and stir well to combine.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on high 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once, until hot.
Stir in sour cream, cheddar cheese, 1/4 chopped green onion and garlic powder.

title: pizz-zanga(pizza-lasagna)
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to package directions.
Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain.
To meat add sauce and seasonings; simmer 20 minutes.
Add cottage cheese to sauce mixture.
In lasagna pan layer the following times three: sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese and grated cheese.
On top add the rest of sausage, optional onion, peppers and mushrooms, pepperoni, cheese and grated cheese.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake until cheese is melted and hot throughout dish, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler with the water added. (May be melted in microwave).
Add pecans and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by 1/2 to 1 tablespoon.
Let cool.

title: mom's chicken soup
directions: Place chicken wings into a 4-quart Dutch oven; fill with water.
Add onion, chicken cubes and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; add rice and return to a boil.
Reduce to medium and cover.
Remove skin and cut up chicken and return to pot.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Enjoy!

title: campers breakfast
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Drain all but 4 tablespoons drippings and add hash browns to skillet; mix well. Cook about 10 minutes, or until browned.
Make 10 wells evenly spaced on top of potatoes.
Place 1 egg in each well, salt and pepper and sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are set.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook chicken until done, then cool and cut into small pieces. Add this to rice, celery, soup, mayonnaise and chestnuts.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with corn flakes mixed with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in buttered 7 x 4-inch pan.
Cover with raw shrimp.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Combine celery soup, salad dressing, lemon juice and cheese.
Spread mixture all over shrimp. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until nice and bubbly.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute garlic, onions, parsley and bell pepper in butter.
Put ground beef and sauteed mixture into saucepan with tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
On side, mix cottage cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
In an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, layer prepared lasagne noodles, cottage cheese, sauce, Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Ricotta and Parmesan cheese.
Cook until cheese is browned and lasagne bubbles.

title: cauliflower morranco
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine with juice of lemon. Saute cauliflower flowerets in margarine with garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow sour cream coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil and 4 eggs.
Mix well.
In another small bowl, mix nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Set aside.

title: emergency cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with hot fudge sauce.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with bread.
Fry loose sausage; drain and sprinkle over bread.
Add cheeses and mushrooms.
Combine slightly beaten eggs with milk and seasonings. Pour over bread, meat and cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: civil war fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice fresh sweet potatoes lengthwise and place in heated iron frying pan with 1/4 inch grease. Fry until golden brown and soft in the middle when poked with a fork. Goes good with sausage or bacon.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour.
Beat with mixer on low until well blended.
Cover bowl tightly and chill for 1 hour or make dough the day before and leave in refrigerator overnight. Shape dough around each unwrapped Kiss.
Be sure Kiss is covered completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet.
Remove and shake in a bag of powdered sugar, or at Christmas, roll in colored sugar before baking.

title: olive or cherry appetizer
directions: Have mother open the container of olives or cherries.
Place them in the plastic bowl.
Place one on end of each 10 fingers and enjoy.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix lemon and cherry jello powder together in a large square bowl.
Bring can of pineapple to boil and pour over jello powder, stirring well.
Then add Coca-Cola and stir well.
Add chopped celery and pecans.
It will be real foamy from Coca-Cola, but that will go away when cooled.
Chill overnight.

title: potato and spinach casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: five layer casserole
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Place several strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 18 pound turkey; roast 25 minutes per pound at 325°.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cranberry sauce in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients, except whipped cream.
Chill until set.
Add whipped cream to chopped up jello.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Boil butter and sugar for a few minutes, then stir in white vinegar.
Keep spooning a few drops of cool water every few seconds.
When drops become crisp upon hitting the water, remove the pan from heat.
Add baking soda and beat until gloss disappears.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and mash potatoes.
Combine potatoes and next 6 ingredients and spoon evenly into 2 lightly greased 9-inch pie plates.
Combine brown sugar, pecans and flour; sprinkle evenly over potato mixture.
Drizzle evenly with 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and frost.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour.
Measure.
Add salt, soda and ginger.
Combine molasses and sour milk.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Add shortening.
Mix well and pour into greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Add glaze if desired or cool in pan about 10 minutes before turning out on rack to cool.
Yield:
One 10-inch tube cake.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put bens in hot worer and cut some sosech up.
Put some rice in a pot and put all the other stuf in and put some sos with it and add worer and cook it.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Mix other ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Mix in the soup mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked christmas tree ornaments
directions: Mix and roll thin.
Cut into shapes desired.
Make hole at top for string or hook.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
After cooled, paint with puffed paints, acrylics, Magic Markers or decorate as desired.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender. Place the rice in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with celery and onions.
Combine ground beef with salt and pepper and brown and drain.
Arrange beef on top of rice and celery.
Combine soup with 1/4 cup water and pour over ground beef.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: 1950 canadian noodle bake
directions: Butter 10 cup casserole and set aside.	Cook noodles as package
directs.	Chop onion finely and add
to
beef;
cook until no color in
beef.
Mix well, about 6 minutes.
Pour mix in bowl and
add
seasonings
and
tomato
juice.
Add noodles (cooked) and stir well.
Add grated cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Place in oven 45 minutes until bubbly at 350°.

title: basic biscuit mix
directions: Blend butter or shortening into other ingredients until small pea-size mixture.
Refrigerate in container with tight lid until ready to use.
Add enough milk to form ball of dough.
Roll out, cut and bake at 375 degrees 10 - 15 minutes.

title: gene's chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In blender, mix peanut butter and milk.
After well blended, add instant pudding and mix for 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour mixture into crust. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chili
directions: Add ingredients in this order, stirring well after each in a large
pot.
Simmer
at least one hour,
stirring often. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients. Add the egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a large baking dish. Sprinkle the brown sugar and nutmeats on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: First Bowl:
Mix lemon and lime jellos with 2 cups boiling water.
Cool and set in refrigerator until slightly cooled.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix cheeses, onions, Worcestershire sauce and Accent together until thoroughly blended. Add 1/2 cup pecans and 1/4 cup parsley.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Place in bowl lined with waxed paper.
Chill overnight. About 1 hour before serving, roll ball in mixture of remaining pecans and parsley.
Place on platter and surround with crisp crackers.
Serve as an hors d'oeuvre or salad accompaniment.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter and press in 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some for topping.
Dissolve jello in water.
Refrigerate until jello begins to harden.
Do not let it set.
Beat with beater the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold jello into this mixture. Then fold in whipped topping and pour over crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by round teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brownie mountain ice cream cake
directions: After your brownies have cooled slightly, you take about 2/3 of the brownies and press them around the sides and bottom of a mixing bowl that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle and press part of the Oreo crumbs into the brownies.
Scoop ice cream and press into the brownie until filled 1/4 from top of brownie.
Take remaining 1/3 brownie and press onto top of ice cream.
Sprinkle and press more Oreo crumbs onto top.
Freeze at least 4 hours or overnight. Before serving, dump bowl upside down onto a plate.
You may need to loosen sides with a knife.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with Oreo crumbs.

title: saratoga pudding
directions: Beat the butter to a thick cream.
Strew in by degrees, the sugar and mix both of these well together.
Then dredge the flour in gradually.
Add the currants and moisten with eggs which should be well beaten.

title: apple pie
directions: Dice apples and mix with sugar. Add cinnamon, flour, salt and vanilla. Pour this mixture into unbaked pie shell and dot top of fruit with 2 teaspoons butter, cut into small bits. Place crust over pie and seal firmly to edge of lower crust, turning edge up slightly to form a ridge. Prepare top crust by cutting air vents to allow steam to escape. Brush top crust with milk or cream and sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: w m pecan brittle
directions: In a large saucepan, mix together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook slowly until candy reaches soft crack stage on candy thermometer.
Add pecans and continue cooking to hard crack stage. Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir thoroughly.
Pour quickly into a buttered pan or platter.
Let cool before serving.

title: snack crackers
directions: Add crackers last and mix well.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar together.
Add milk and flavoring. Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until firm in center, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar and margarine on stove until dissolved.
Beat eggs and add to crumbs and salt.
Add milk mixture.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and raisins.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Put casserole on cookie sheet with water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together vegetables for a toss salad.
Slice olives into mixture.
Crush nachos into medium size pieces and spread over salad.
Mix nachos and cheese into salad.
Pour French dressing over mixture and toss salad just prior to serving.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In bowl, mix dry ingredients with wooden spoon and add melted margarine.
The mixture will be a little lumpy.
Put 1/2 mixture in pan.
Add cherry pie filling, then rest of mixture; spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Dilute lemonade and orangeade according to label directions. mix apricot nectar and pineapple juice; stir in lemonade and orangeade.
Chill.
Stir in sherbet; add ginger ale.
Serve immediately.
Yields 50 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups and water together in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Place chicken pieces on top.
Season with seasoned salt and dill weed sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours uncovered.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Bake brownies according to directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In separate bowl, whip your cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Then add peanut butter and half of your whipped cream; beat until there's a creamy texture.
Let brownies cool completely, then spread peanut butter mixture on top and use the remaining whipped cream on top.
Crush Reese's cup up into small pieces and sprinkle on top.

title: kahlua
directions: Steep coffee in 1 1/2 quarts of boiling water.
Combine the sugar and 1 quart boiled water and cook for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Mix coffee and sugar mixtures together.
Add vanilla, alcohol and 1/2 fifth more water to make 1 gallon.
May be served over cracked ice or vanilla ice cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: suet cake for birds
directions: Stir dry ingredients and then add melted suet and mix well. Pack into styrofoam cups through which a knotted cord has been drawn like a candlewick.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Peel off upper half of cup and hang in tree or bush.

title: pecan delights
directions: Whip butter until soft and add the confectioners sugar.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and water.
Roll into balls.
Put on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Remove bones and chop into cubes. Grease casserole dish.
Layer the following:
Doritos, soaked in chicken broth, chicken, onion, seasoning, all soups and cheese. Top with Ro-Tel.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
Combine margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg; cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in raisins.
Drop by tablespoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 15 minute cream fettuccini alfredo
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add fettuccini and toss lightly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: maple walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven 450°.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add everything else except nuts; stir until moistened.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour in paper lined muffin tins until full.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: heavenly hash pie
directions: Blend milk, lemon juice, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: pumpkin cream dessert
directions: Combine pudding mix, spice, milk, egg and pumpkin.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture boils.
Cool 5 minutes and then pour on crust.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well and shape into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve on crackers or celery sticks.

title: meat and tater tots casserole
directions: Brown meat and then press evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle dry onion and Accent over meat.
Mix soups and spread over meat.
Place Tater Tots as close together as possible over top. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Bake 1/2 hour longer to crisp the Tater Tots.
Serves 8.

title: florey's special steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 150° (to keep steaks warm while preparing the "special" sauce).
Cook two steaks at a time.
Heat half the oil in a large skillet.
Add the steaks and cook for 5 minutes over high heat.
Turn, season with salt and pepper and cook for another 5 minutes for medium.
Remove steaks and keep in oven.
Repeat using the remaining oil for the other two steaks.
Add shallots, garlic, parsley, butter and mushrooms to skillet.
Season with salt and pepper and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Pour in cognac and cook about 3 minutes over high heat.
Add cream and Tabasco.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Mix in the lemon juice and serve over the steaks.
A fine Bordeaux, Cabernet Sauvignon or a Rhone Valley wine would go quite well.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: In greased baking dish place half of stuffing, meat seasoned with salt and pepper and half of soup.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk. Fold in fruits and nuts. Pour into a large tube pan or several small loaf pans. Bake at 300° (tube pan) for 2 hours or at 325° (loaf pans) for 1 hour.

title: marinated 3 bean salad
directions: Drain canned beans.
In large bowl, combine lima beans, green beans, red kidney beans, onion rings and green pepper.
In a screw top jar, combine vinegar, salad oil, sugar and celery seed; cover and shake well.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and stir lightly.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cantonese lobster
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook sausage and garlic together until the sausage is
no	longer pink.
Add broth and bring to boil. Turn heat low
and	skim off fat.
Add lobster, ginger, salt and pepper to
taste.
Turn
heat
up again and add cornstarch (mixed with
water)
to thicken sauce.
Add beaten eggs and cook another 5 minutes.	Serve over hot rice.
May garnish with chopped green onion, if desired.

title: my man's cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat. Sift together the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients to the shortening mixture.
Gradually, while beating, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheets.
Flatten a little with a fork.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: buffet stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in butter until brown; add mushrooms, peppers and onions.
Saute.
Add beef stock (if beef stock is made from cubes, reduce salt to 1/2 teaspoon).
Simmer 15 minutes; mix flour with sour cream.
Add to beef mixture, stirring well to thicken. Simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given.
Add the sugar to the salad dressing; spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with the grated cheese.
Cover; put in refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours.
Serve.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In a frying pan, blend cornstarch with cold water.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Boil a few minutes until clear, stirring constantly.
Add butter, sliced onions, diced bacon and sliced potatoes.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, Karo syrup and oleo or butter together.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take baking soda and add to syrup mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring a few times.

title: southwestern bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, saving 2 tablespoons drippings. Remove and crumble bacon.
Cook onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons drippings until soft.
Stir in beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and crumbled bacon.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 2 slices uncooked bacon (optional).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Shape into ball and chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside. Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Combine egg and buttermilk. Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Dredge in flour mixture, coating well.
Place chicken in baking dish, turning once to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: california rice skillet
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add rice, water, bouillon, onion, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until rice is done. Meanwhile, dice green pepper and tomato; stir in.
Put Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Cover and cook until cheese is melted.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Add salt and dressing.
Cover with foil and bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; baste and bake chicken until lightly brown.
Serve over rice if desired.

title: cointreau balls
directions: Form into very small balls.
Roll in fine granulated sugar. Put into tightly covered tin until you are ready to eat them.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wash and salt breasts.
Combine wine, sour cream, soup and flour.
Use flat pan; layer chicken and pour mixture on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
(You can also use slivered almonds.)

title: yum yums
directions: Melt margarine and caramels; add Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat.
Place a toothpick in each marshmallow; dip into mixture.
Roll in Rice Krispies.
Place each marshmallow into a cupcake paper; let set 10 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls and then in sugar. Put on pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash. Mix butter with cornbread stuffing. Mix squash, carrot, onion, sour cream, soup and 1/2 the stuffing. Place into a baking dish and cover with remaining stuffing. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: In small bowl, mix dry ingredients and set aside.
In large bowl, mix sugar, vanilla, eggs, oil and milk at medium speed for about 2 minutes.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix for about 2 more minutes.
Add carrots and pineapple (with juice).
Pour into greased baking pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: parmigiano reggiano baked chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pound the chicken breasts lightly with a meat mallet to flatten them. Season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Cook 3 of the cutlets until golden brown on each side. Remove from the pan and reserve. Repeat with the remaining oil and cutlets. Transfer cutlets to a casserole dish. Evenly distribute the Prosciutto, parsley and cheese to cover each cutlet. Then sprinkle with the Marsala. Bake in oven until cheese melts through. Serve immediately.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Mix together milk and unthawed lemonade. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Pour into pie crust. Chill overnight.

title: they'll never forget your cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Form ball and roll in crushed nuts.
Makes 1 very large or 2 small cheese balls.

title: hot buttered lemonade(antifreeze for cold winter days)
directions: Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Pour into mugs and top with 1 teaspoon butter.
Serve with cinnamon stick stirrers.

title: ham delights
directions: Melt margarine with last 4 ingredients.
Using a large knife, slice the tops off entire pan of party rolls at one time, leaving bottom of rolls in original container.
Spread with slices of ham and cheese.
Replace top half.
Pour butter mixture on top of rolls.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: better than anything chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and pecans in large mixing bowl. Beat slightly only until mixture is combined. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch fluted Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat.
Add comino, oregano and garlic powder.
Add chili mix and enchilada mix.
Pour warm water over this, about 1 quart. Put oil in skillet with medium heat.
Place 1 corn tortilla in oil and turn over and take out, just long enough for it to be soft, not cooked.
Put on plate and repeat with 12 to 15 corn tortillas. Blot with paper towel.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water to cover (add a pinch of baking soda) overnight.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Add ham bone and simmer until beans are tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Remove the ham bone, pull off all bits of meat and return to the soup pot.
Add vegetables and simmer another hour.
Place remaining ingredients in soup pot (except the parsley) the last 10 minutes of cooking. You may find it necessary to add water during cooking.
The goal is to have a thick, not watery broth.
Garnish with parsley.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/2 lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
Cook stuffing as directed on package.
Place cooked stuffing in scooped-out area.
Sprinkle with your favorite shredded cheese. Wrap in foil.
Bake until tender.
(Time depends on size of zucchini, large takes about 1 hour.)

title: maple walnut pie
