directions: In large bowl, ceam together sugar and butter.
Mix eggs in, one at a time.
Mix in corn syrup and maple syrup.
Add the quick oats.
Mix in the walnuts and vanilla.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Filling will appear soft; will set as it cools.

title: chris' chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Combine onions and garlic with remaining ingredients in a double boiler.
Heat on low temperature until cheese is melted, stirring frequently. Serve with big dip Fritos corn chips.

title: mrs. fogg's vegetable dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add vegetables, sour cream, soup, almonds, 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole; top with 1/2 cup crushed crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes (or microwave on High for 20 minutes) until bubbly.
Serve hot.
May be prepared up to 2 days ahead, then heated.
Serves 8.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Place halved muffins on cookie sheet.
Spread with sauce. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Place under broiler for 1 minute or until cheese bubbles.
Wrap muffins in foil to keep warm until you serve.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in heavy skillet until tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, venison, salt and pepper.
Simmer until thickened, stirring frequently.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine ingredients except sherbet and ginger ale.
Can be mixed day before and stored in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Sherbet takes a little time to melt. Serves 50.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sprinkle diced apples with 1 cup sugar; set aside.
Beat eggs and remaining cup of sugar. Add oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Continue beating until well mixed.
Add vanilla, apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Put ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except biscuits.
Simmer about 20 minutes. Pour into casserole dish; top with biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are brown at 375°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix the spaghetti,
onion, green pepper, cucumber and tomatoes together. Add the Italian dressing and Salad Supreme. Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: chicken with parmesan cheese and garlic
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over and bake 1 hour.
Sprinkle on additional cheese when served.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper in a skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Layer onion, potatoes and green pepper over ground beef.
Top with soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and put cheese on top.
Put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix together and pour over any fruit.

title: stuffed eggplant with shrimp
directions: Peel eggplant; take out as many seeds as you can with spoon. Cut into blocks; add to boiling water.
When tender, drain, saving some liquid.
In another pot, put oil and butter and melt.
Add vegetables and cook until wilted.
Add shrimp and ham and saute on slow fire for 1/2 hour.
Add eggplant, rest of seasoning and bread crumbs and simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring constantly.
If it appears dry, add some eggplant water.
Add cayenne and salt to taste.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler or microwave.
Add noodles and peanuts; stir.
Spoon out on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mini-meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 of the tomato sauce. Shape into 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon reserved tomato sauce over meatballs.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 8 to 9 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 4 minutes before serving.
Yields 35 meatballs.

title: bacon-cheese quiche squares
directions: Separate crescent rolls into two rectangles.
Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of pan to form crust. Seal perforations.

Sprinkle cheeses over dough. Combine egg, onion, milk, olives and mushroom pieces. Pour over cheeses. Sprinkle with bacon bits and parsley. Bake at 357° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes and cut into squares. Recipe is easily doubled and baked on cookie sheet.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Place egg white and water in large bowl. Beat until frothy but not stiff. Pour pecans into egg white and stir until coated.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; lay in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Pour undiluted soup over meatballs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir and turn over so they brown on both sides.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Lightly spoon flour into cup; level off.
In large bowl blend ingredients; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding and mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies.
Pour into a large bowl and top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Quick and delicious!

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in oil, then add ground beef and brown in 10-inch skillet or saucepan.
Add tomato sauce, hot water, salt and garlic salt; bring to a boil.
Break spaghetti in half, add to the ingredients.
Reduce heat to barely boiling.
Stir frequently and cook 12 to 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, butter and salt in pan; bring to a boil slowly.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil over medium heat until soft ball stage (236° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat; let stand 15 minutes.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture starts to loose gloss (may take 5 to 8 minutes).
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour quickly into greased shallow pan.
Cool and then cut into squares.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep six weeks.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: oriental pork
directions: Cook
pieces
of
tenderloin
on
low heat in frypan in melted butter.
Brown lightly and add salt, pepper, soy sauce, cream, fruit cocktail and juice, diced pickles, mushrooms and bouillon cubes.
Cook
on
low heat for 1/2 hour until bubbly. Serve over rice.
Serves 6 people.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour in casserole dish. Mix together next 3 ingredients and pour on top of casserole. Place nuts on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in given order.
Make in small balls; press down with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cold crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve very cold.

title: hot beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan and cook until thickened (except rice and salt).
Serve over a bed of rice.
This is a very good dish.
I do not put salt in my beans until they are soft. Seems like salt toughens the skin.

title: corn fritters
directions: Shuck corn and rinse with water.
In large cooker, boil water (boil water before adding corn).
Blanch small ears for 7 minutes in boiling water.
Blanch medium ears for 9 minutes.
Blanch large ears for 11 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Place in airtight bags and freeze.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour muffin tins. Thoroughly combine flour, apples, sugar, egg, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Pour batter into muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: hot tamales
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well by hand.
Take about 1 tablespoon at a time.
Roll in yellow corn meal or masa. Wrap in papers.
Wet papers first so they will not be stiff.
Take string and tie 3 tamales together at a time.
Put tamales in large roasting pan.
Pour boiling water to completely cover all the tamales.
To the pot, add 1 can tomato sauce and 1 ounce chili powder.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.

title: no run meringue for cream pies
directions: Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add vanilla and 6 tablespoons sugar, small amount at a time. Add thickener; beat 3 minutes longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed potatoes, onion, soup, cheese and 2 tablespoons of melted margarine. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar.
Add butter and mix well.
Press mixture in 9-inch spring-form pan (sides and bottom).
Save a few crumbs for top of cake.
Chill.
When chilled, add 20 ounces of strained crushed pineapple.

title: three layer dinner
directions: Shred cabbage and put half of it
in the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Next add 1/2 potatoes and 1/2 of the hamburger. Salt and pepper each layer.
Add remaining ingredients in order, having hamburger on top. Add milk and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour in pastry shell. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: seafood stuffed tomatoes
directions: Combine rice, shrimp, crabmeat, eggs, celery, pepper, onion, pickles and pimentos in a bowl. Set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in 2 1/2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil; stir constantly about 5 minutes.
Test in cold water, when small amount forms soft ball, remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: texas grapefruit cake
directions: Sift
dry ingredients into bowl (except sugar).
Strain and combine grapefruit juice with oil.
Separate eggs and beat whites to stiff peaks.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick. Beat in about
cup flour mix with 1/4 juice mix.
Repeat until
all is used.
Gently fold in beaten whites.
Pour into two
9-inch floured
cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with two slices of dried beef.
Place in a casserole dish.
Layer bacon on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While chicken is baking, mix mushroom soups and sour cream in a saucepan.
Warm until just starting to bubble. Pour over baked chicken and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: fish in beer batter
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in bowl and beat lightly.
Dip fish in batter to coat.
Cook in pan with hot shortening or butter until brown.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Add cubed bread.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve as side dish with baked ham or as a dessert with whipped topping.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into thin strips.
Heat oil in large frying pan. Brown meat.
Add 2 cups water and simmer until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook 5 minutes additional.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add slowly to hot mixture to thicken.
Add tomatoes to warm.
Serve over cooked rice or boiled noodles.

title: appetizer pizza
directions: Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place on bottom and sides of greased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing together to form crust.
Saute onion, zucchini and mushrooms in margarine.
Combine cream cheese, milk, egg and salt, mixing until well blended.
Stir in vegetables.
Pour over crust and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time (medium mixer speed).
Mix dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream.
End with dry ingredients.
Add almond flavor.
Grease an angel food pan.
Put in layer of batter. Swirl in sauce and nuts.
Repeat, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion.
Heat sauce mix and tomato sauce until bubbly.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Mix in sour cream (place in dollops over top and stir).
Put Mozzarella on top of this.
Place dinner rolls on top of cheese.
Brush tops of rolls with melted butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until rolls are brown.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Bring 3/4 full pan of water to boil in bottom pan of double boiler. Combine 1/2 c sugar, flour, and salt in top pan of a double boiler. Beat egg yolks and milk together, add to flour mixture; blend well. Place over boiling water,

cook, uncovered, stirring constantly till thickened. Reduce heat, cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 min. Remove from heat, stir in vanilla extract. Spread small amount of custard in bottom of a 2 qt. casserole dish. Layer wafers, bananas, and custard. Repeat for total of 3 layers, ending with custard. Set aside. In a grease free bowl, beat egg whites till stiff but not dry. Add remaining 1.4 c sugar, beat till stiff peaks form. Spread over pudding, sealing edges. Bake at 450° for 5 min. Cool before serving. When I make this recipe, I double the pudding recipe and add more bananas. I also use the wafer crumbs in the bottom of the package to sprinkle on top of the meringue.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients as listed and cook at 350° until done. Cooking time will be approximately 40 minutes.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add boiling water; let it cool.
Add egg to date mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; mix into date mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: june's orange glazed beets
directions: Heat and bring to boil the margarine, sugar, orange juice, orange rind and vinegar.
Cook 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with water and stir into sauce.
Cook until thickened and clear.
Add beets and simmer 10 minutes.

title: trash candy
directions: Pour mixture over the ingredients mixed in a large bowl.
Stir with a wooden spoon and drop on waxed paper.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Make into meatballs.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with onions and peppers.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, water, vinegar and sugar.
Pour mixture over meatballs and cook 45 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: great jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate meat in a tightly covered glass, stoneware, stainless steel or plastic container for 6 to 12 hours in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
This is enough marinade for 1 pound beef or venison.
Meat should be lean and sliced 3/16 to 1/4-inch thick.

title: buche de noel (christmas chocolate roll)(holiday)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Line it with waxed paper, extending 4-inches beyond the ends of the pan. Butter the waxed paper and set it aside. Wet a towel and squeeze it until it is damp-dry.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing just until blended.
Stir in peaches and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Carefully melt chocolate in microwave or double boiler.
Mix peanut butter and sugar.
Shape into small patties.
Put 1 teaspoon melted chocolate in bottoms of cupcake wrappers.
Let harden.
Place peanut butter patty on top of chocolate.
Pour 3 teaspoons melted chocolate over top to form the top and sides of cup; let harden in cool place.
Do not place in refrigerator.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add milk; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat with wooden spoon vigorously until very thick.
Pour into a 9-inch pan; cool before cutting into small squares.

title: lavender mist
directions: Fill your bottles with only distilled water and you have a spray for ironing or bed pillows.
Enjoy spring.

title: fresh melon and fresh figs and prosciutto
directions: Peel and seed the melon. Cut into bite-sized cubes; coat each cube with freshly chopped parsley. Wrap with a strip of Prosciutto; fasten with toothpick. Grind a dusting of black pepper over Prosciutto. Wash the figs and slice in half lengthwise. Follow as for the melon, ending with a dusting of black pepper.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut each stalk of celery into 4 pieces.
Place peanut butter in small bowl.
Add cheese spread.
Mix together well.
Spread mixture into each celery piece, using butter knife.
Arrange 3 or 4 raisins "ants" on peanut butter mixture.
Serve right away or cover and store in refrigerator for up to 2 hours.

title: kolaches
directions: Heat milk, add shortening or oleo to dissolve; let cool to lukewarm.
Add salt, egg yolks (slightly beaten) and sugar.
Add all to yeast (which at this time should have risen to a foamy stage).
If you place the yeast and liquid in a large bowl, you are ready to add flour a little at a time until all is used up.
Work dough either by mixer or hand until it is glossy.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about an hour.
Dough will not be as thick as used in dinner rolls (with some flour you may have to add 1/4 cup more).

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients in bowl until crumbly.
Stir in egg and yogurt until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins.
(Use any flavor yogurt for variety.)

title: best raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Stir in orange juice and water gradually, stirring until smooth. Add orange rind, butter and raisins. Set over high heat and bring to a boil quickly, stirring constantly. Turn down heat and cook gently 3 minutes more, stirring. Remove and cool.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In large bowl, gradually stir soup into milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover tightly and microwave on High 10 minutes.
Stir; cover and microwave on High 10 to 15 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Stuff into 6 or 8 green peppers.
Put in baking dish with lid.
Add one can of tomato sauce and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be served with Parmesan cheese.

title: when you don't have much time, cook this...
directions: Fry the ground turkey and drain.
Mix with tomatoes and corn. Heat on medium-low for about 1/2 hour and serve.
Great with corn bread!

title: cajun millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in a double boiler with water; add pecans.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Drop onto waxed paper in bite-sized pieces; chill in refrigerator overnight.
Melt chocolate candy in double boiler.
Dip pieces of chilled candy in chocolate mixture and let dry.

title: fast fixin' fruit 'n' cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add the 4 egg yolks and 2 whites, beaten together.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer. Sift flour with soda added.
Add flour mixture to first mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans that have been greased and floured.
(I use four 8-inch pans.)
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 large layers or 4 smaller layers.

title: shells with tuna, broccoli and red onion
directions: Heat olive oil in a medium skillet over low heat; stir in onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes (garlic shouldn't brown and onion should still be crunchy).
Off heat, add the tuna, lemon juice, parsley, lemon zest, oregano and black pepper.
Cook the shells in plenty of boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Add the broccoli; cook until pasta is al dente, or firm to the bite, and broccoli is tender, 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Remove 1/4 cup of the pasta cooking water and add to the tuna sauce.
Drain pasta; toss with tuna mixture and serve at once.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in a covered container. Use 2 to 4 teaspoons per cup or mug.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Microwave until tender the zucchini, squash, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Spread 1/2 cup pasta sauce over bread. Layer cooked vegetables.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Top with sliced tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mom's stuffed sauerkraut
directions: Mix pork, sausage, onion, eggs, salt and cooked rice and make into meatballs.
Lightly rinse sauerkraut; layer sauerkraut, then meatballs alternately until all is used.
Add 1 cup water (pouring over all).
Bake or preferably cook on top of stove (until water is gone) with a lid.
Gravy can be poured over entire dish for added seasoning.

title: hash browns deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 can onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cocktail smoky links or meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly in a crock pot.
Heat thoroughly, stirring gently often.

title: marinade for beef
directions: For marinade combine first 9 ingredients.
Pour over beef; cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cook beef on a grill, using the marinade as a basting sauce.

title: chocolate-laced kiwi fruit with orange sauce
directions: Mix yogurt and orange juice concentrate; spoon 2 tablespoons onto each of 4 dessert plates.
Arrange 1 sliced kiwi fruit over yogurt mixture on each plate.
Heat chocolate chips and shortening over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Carefully drizzle chocolate in thin lines over kiwi fruit.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix well; refrigerate.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour pan.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Crust will be darker than regular layer cake.

title: grandma annie webster tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Work enough flour into dough to be able to roll out with rolling pin.
Cut with cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place in 8 x 8-inch pan on bottom the chicken and Swiss cheese slices.
Spread cream of celery soup and Stove Top stuffing mixed up.
Drizzle melted butter over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: baked beans, boston style
directions: Soak and simmer beans.
Turn into a bean pot or heavy casserole without draining.
Combine salt, brown sugar, molasses and mustard with 1 cup boiling water and pour over beans.
Scrape rind of salt pork and cut gashes into fat 1/2-inch apart.
Press into the beans leaving only rind exposed.
Cover pot and bake in slow oven (250° to 275°) for 6 to 8 hours, adding more water as needed to keep beans moist.
Remove cover for last half hour of baking.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook sugar, butter and water for 5 minutes.
Add carrots and cook until hot.
Serves 6.

title: tater casserole
directions: Mix beef like meat loaf.
Place in a dish.
Put soup on top; then add a layer of cut green beans.
Add a layer of Tater Tots. You can add onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies with walnuts
directions: Mix and drop on baking sheet from spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, eggs, Parmesan cheese, and butter and press into 10 inch pie plate.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Place a layer of bread crumbs in a greased casserole.
Add a layer of chicken, parsley and seasonings.
Alternate layers, ending with bread crumbs on top.
Beat eggs; add milk and broth. Pour over mixture and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: priscilla's perky pilaf
directions: *Whole grain cereal found in health stores.

title: lemon congealed salad
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows in a medium saucepan over low heat, stirring until marshmallows melt.
Add gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Combine cream cheese, pineapple, and pecans.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Let cool completely.
Beat whipping cream at medium speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into lightly greased dish.
Chill 6 hours.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water on medium heat to 300°. Remove from heat. Add red food coloring and cinnamon oil. Stir. Pour into 2 buttered 16 x 15 x 1-inch pans. Cool and break into pieces.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and egg.
Pat lightly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon powdered sugar before cake cools.

title: chicken aloha
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients except rice; pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jamaican punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into glasses over ice.

title: apple-cheese casserole
directions: Place apples in casserole dish and top with cheese.
In separate bowl, mix margarine, flour and sugar.
Dabble over apples.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes or until dough is brown.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Pressure cook chicken
and
bone.
Heat
soups together with one can water and the green chilies.
Stuff each tortilla with chicken, soup
mixture
and
cheese.
Pour remaining soup mixture and cheese over enchiladas.
Makes 2 (11 x 7 x 2-inch) baking dishes.
Heat in warm 300° oven until cheese is melted.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch dish, combine the first 4 ingredients, but use only 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk; pour over other ingredients.
Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: In blender, combine berries, milk, yogurt and orange juice concentrate; blend smooth and pour into a tall glass.
Slip a whole berry on the lip of the glass and you have a pretty as well as a nutritious drink.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an 8 x 12-inch or 10-inch square baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and egg until lumpy.
Spread this mixture over the peaches.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar
and
flour in a skillet. Stir in milk or water. Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and butter together.
Place in casserole dish. Drain broccoli and place over this mixture.
Spread jar of Cheez Whiz over broccoli and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pioneer sugar cookies
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples, then run through colander.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in oven and cook done to thickness of your liking.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine first three (3) ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly brown. Sprinkle with extra powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend first 5 items together well and pour in a 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top, then add chopped nuts over top.
Dribble melted butter over the top.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle jello on cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Can be served immediately or refrigerated.

title: baked bananas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Peel large firm bananas; cut lengthwise in half.
Place halves, cut side down, in greased baking dish.
Brush with lemon juice.
Sprinkle each half with 1/2 teaspoon grated lemon peel and 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar.
Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain off fat. Add all ingredients. Simmer on top of stove for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan 3 times to coat with the vegetable oil.
Put the mustard, paprika, cumin, chili powder and cayenne pepper in a large bowl.
Whisk to blend. Prick the potatoes several times with the tines of a fork and add them to the bowl.
Toss to coat the potatoes evenly.
Pour the coated potatoes into the prepared roasting pan, leaving a little space between them.
Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until the potatoes are fork-tender.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large pan.
Bring to boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add other ingredients and mix well. Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream all ingredients (except preserves) in the order in which they are listed.
Remove 3/4 cup of mix and reserve for topping. Pat batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until a small brown edge forms.
Remove from oven and spread with 8 ounces apricot preserves.
Sprinkle with the reserved topping.
Return to oven for 25 minutes.
It is done when bubbly and brown.
Cut into bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine both cans of corn.
Add the egg to the corn.
Add the cream cheese.
Add the cornbread mix.
Pour into two greased 9-inch pie pans.
Pour melted butter over.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter, then set aside.
Blend together boxes of pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Add both mixtures together.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and add apricot brandy, almond extract and vodka.
This can be darkened by adding food coloring (3 drops green, 9 drops red and 12 drops yellow).
Comes out like a sable brown color.
Serve over ice or in cream.

title: creek potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Layer bacon, potatoes and onion along with salt and pepper.
Cook in oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until well blended. Mix gelatine with water.
Add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in mold and let set overnight.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables or crackers.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, cheese, parsley and milk in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: my barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and pour over seasoned, browned ribs or chicken and simmer until sauce is thick.

title: pickled beans
directions: You will also need 15 pint jars.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat; beat in peanut butter.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: hot sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wrap bread sticks with bacon strips in peppermint-stripe fashion.
Roll in cheese and bake until golden brown.

title: million dollar brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and stir in cocoa, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, vinegar, oil, celery seed and dry mustard.
Bring ingredients to a boil and pour over the cabbage, pepper and onion.
Let stand at least 6 hours.
Keep in refrigerator after it cools.
Delicious after staying in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salsa, tomato paste and cumin.
Mix into ground beef mixture. Mix together well.
Press meat mixture into buttered 9-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions; stir in cheese.
Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is cooked through and lightly browned.

title: alice peedin sweet pickles
directions: Wash small cucumbers.
Pack in glass gallon jar.
Put as many as possible in jar.
Using a thin cloth, place spices and salt in middle and tie with string or thread.
Place this in middle of jar, while packing cucumbers.
Cover with vinegar.
Put lid on tightly.
Let stand 6 weeks.
Remove vinegar and spices.
Slice cucumbers, layering with sugar until all is used.
Let sit, stirring until sugar is melted.
Leave overnight.
Place pickles in jars.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let cool.
Cream together shortening, soda, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add dates and water. Mix as for muffins with flour and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts. Grease and flour Number 303 cans.
Fill 2/3 full of mixture and bake at 375° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger well and drain.
Chop onion and green pepper. Mix all ingredients together with meat.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove and let cool.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add the beaten eggs.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mold into a loaf and let stand in icebox for 24 hours.
Slice and bake in 375° oven.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine oatmeal, 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar and salt; mix well.
Stir in margarine; mix until well blended.
Set 1 cup aside to be used later.
Press remaining into bottom of greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: odessa's stuffed bell pepper
directions: Wash and core peppers; mix other ingredients and fill peppers. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
These can be wrapped and frozen.
Just reheat to serve.
This mixture can be used as a casserole.
Also, just leave off 7 of the peppers and chop one and add to other mixture and in casserole bake for 2 hours at 325° or until done.

title: nut goodie candy
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
This will be soft but hardens quickly if put in refrigerator.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients but nuts in pan. Stir together over medium heat.
Bring to boil, simmer until forms ball (drop in water).
Takes about 15 minutes. Then remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Turn out on wax paper or cookie sheet. Rapidly separate with 2 forks.
Cool.
Eat.
You can't stop, they are so good.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Put mayonnaise in mixing bowl.
Add salad oil, a few drops at a time, beating constantly.
Blend in well the half & half, garlic, oregano, worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bean dip
directions: Shred cheese and set 1/2 cup aside.
Chop 3 or 4 onions.
Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle the 1/2 cup of saved cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: cheerio snacks
directions: Cook margarine and brown sugar until syrupy in saucepan.
Add to Cheerios, unsalted peanuts and broken pecans.
Mix all together well.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Spread mixture on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Oil another large cookie sheet and pour mixture immediately onto it.
Cool at room temperature. Store in airtight container.

title: celery pinwheels
directions: Clean celery and separate branches.
Blend together the softened cream cheese with the Roquefort cheese.
Add mayonnaise to make the mixture of spreading consistency and season with a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Fill the branches of celery with cheese mixture.
Press branches back into the original form of the stalk.
Roll in waxed paper and chill overnight in refrigerator. Just before serving, slice celery crosswise forming pinwheels. Arrange pinwheels on crisp lettuce for serving.

title: garden tossed salad
directions: Wash and dry chicory and/or red leaf lettuce.
Slice cucumbers, sliver peppers, chop onions, chop celery, halve mushrooms and tear parsley.
Mix and chill.
Just before serving, add salt to taste and a pinch of sugar.
Dress with oil and vinegar sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Garnish with olives, Feta cheese and radishes.

title: zucchini raisin cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in zucchini; set aside.
Combine flour, baking soda, spices, baking powder and salt.
Add to zucchini mixture and stir until thoroughly combined.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until golden brown for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool in pans for 2 minutes before removing to wire rack.
Cookies are cake like. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, potatoes, peas and carrots, spices and enough potato water to make right sauce consistency. (You may also use white sauce or thicken vegetable water with flour and milk.) Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix last 3 ingredients and pour thin batter over top. Bake in 450° oven until batter is cooked.

title: methodist punch
directions: Use only pink Hawaiian punch.
Triple the recipe and it will serve 200 or more.
Mix one recipe at a time.

title: chocolate pudding cheese pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, milk and pie filling mix together until smooth and creamy.
Pour into the baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until blended and smooth.
Fold in orange juice, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 2 cups.
Use as dip for fresh fruit, pretzel sticks, cake squares, cookies. etc.
Contains about 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: liver and onions
directions: Put flour in bowl or dish or pan with salt and pepper added to flour, or you can put right on liver.
Put skillet on stove with oil and bacon in it.
Fry bacon for about 5 minutes, then take out or leave in.
Put floured liver in skillet and fry until brown on both sides, turning often.
After browned, slice up onion on liver and pour water on.
Cover and let cook about 20 minutes on low heat.
Serve, it's so good.
(The bacon cuts the taste of the liver.)

title: butter pecan delight
directions: Crumble 60 Ritz crackers and combine with 1/2 stick butter (melted).
Save 1 cup for topping.
Place rest in 9 x 13-inch pan and press down with fork.
Mix milk with instant vanilla pudding. Add butter pecan softened ice cream to pudding, then spread over crackers.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine dry ingredients, mixing well.
Dip chicken in milk and dredge in flour mixture.
Heat one inch of oil in electric skillet to 325°.
Add chicken and fry 5 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 dozen nuggets.

title: grated carrot casserole(tastes just like sweet potato souffle)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in melted margarine and vanilla. Combine eggs and milk; whisk lightly. Combine both mixtures with carrots. Pour into a greased baking dish. Cook in oven for 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cover with topping.

title: sauteed sesame fish
directions: Beat egg in shallow bowl.
In second bowl, mix bread crumbs and sesame seed.
Dip fillets into egg, then coat with crumb mixture.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook fish on medium heat until golden on both sides (turning once), about 5 minutes.

title: greek salad(horiatiki)
directions: You can use your desired quantities of ingredients.

title: chocolate scotch-oat cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together the oleo and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mix and mix well.
Stir in oats and both kinds of chips.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water.
When soft add sugar and cook over slow heat for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling mixture over Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Chill, when partially set add celery, nuts and apple.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place first four ingredients in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350" for 45 minutes.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: Rinse pork chops.
Place in bag along with flour, salt and pepper.
Coat well.
Place enough olive oil to cover bottom of frying pan.
Fry 20 minutes on each side on medium-high heat. Turn down to low and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until blended together.
Stir in the cornflakes.
Keeping hands moist, roll into balls.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and sugar.
Add cereal; mix lightly until well coated. Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch SilverStone pan (or lightly greased pan). Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
48 squares.

title: chuck roast
directions: Brown roast in cooking oil.
Remove roast and add flour, making thick paste.
Add water, A.1. steak and Worcestershire sauce.
Place meat in liquid and cover.
Cook on top of stove for 3 to 4 hours or until meat is tender.
Water may be added as needed.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate both cans of dough into 16 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausage on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up each, starting at short side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown, switching position of cookie sheets halfway through baking.
Serve warm.

title: teddy's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Stir into batter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Turn into buttered and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool before turning out.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Spray a
x
13-inch	Pyrex dish with Pam.
Line dish with white
bread,
torn
in
small
pieces.
Brown 1 pound of sausage with mushrooms.
Pour this over bread.
Beat the eggs; add milk, cheese,
salt
and pepper.	Pour this over layer of sausage and mushrooms.	Cover with foil and put in refrigerator overnight. Bake
for
minutes
to 1 hour until middle looks done.	Bake at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough until done in pizza pan.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of baked, cooled cookie dough.
Add pineapple and other fruits.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: matzo brei
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Run sheets matzah under cold water. Mix eggs in bowl. Add onion powder, salt and pepper. Soak broken matzah sheets in eggs for 5 minutes. Pour egg/matzah mixture into heated skillet. Cook over medium/high. Serve immediately. Salt and pepper to taste or syrup.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti until done.
Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper and drain.
Add Ro-Tel, Mexican corn and tomato soup.
Cook until boiling.
Add spaghetti to the mixture and mix well.
Then place cheese slices on top to cover the mixture.
Let melt.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3-quart dish.
Brown beef and drain fat.
Add salsa, cumin and salt.
Simmer until thick and all liquid is absorbed.
Place mixture in dish and top with onions, 2 cups cheese, beans, olives and remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Spoon onto lettuce and top with tomato.
Serve tortilla chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Form sausage in patties.
Brown and drain.
Crumble in pieces.
Add chopped onion, pepper and celery.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Cook noodle soup in the 1 cup of water for 10 minutes.
Then add to the sausage mixture.
Add cooked rice, almonds and mushrooms.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: astrid's apple nobby cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and butter.
Add beaten egg and mix well. Add apples,
spices,
flour,
baking
soda and baking powder. Pour into
greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. When cool, serve with whipped cream.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in a skillet and add shrimp, lobster, garlic and green pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes. Transfer contents of skillet to a casserole dish.
In a small bowl mix together wine, lemon juice, egg, mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Beat until well blended.
Gently fold crabmeat and bread crumbs into liquid.
Pour mixture over seafood in casserole and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: *If using a tart vinegar, add 2 teaspoons sugar.

title: dip
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Drain tomatoes.
Melt cheese and mix sausage and tomatoes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Heat broth and soups; pour over chicken.

title: confetti dip
directions: Beat with a fork in saucepan the eggs, vinegar and sugar. Cook over low heat until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Mix with beaters the cream cheese with a little milk.
When smooth, add cooled custard mixture, olives, chopped pimentos, bell pepper and onion.
Mix thoroughly.

title: molasses pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add flour, ginger and vinegar; blend well.
Mix in molasses.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Egg whites and sugar may be made into meringue.
Spread on the hot pie and brown in oven for 5 minutes at 425° or until lightly brown.
If you don't like meringue use whipped cream or a small scoop of ice cream.

title: stuffed french toast ala kootch
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut bread into cubes.
Cube the cream cheese.
Place 1/2 the bread in
9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spray with Pam.
Place cream cheese on top of bread and top with remaining bread.
In a large
bowl, beat eggs with a whisk and add the syrup and milk and whisk until well mixed.
Pour over bread. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Remove the plastic wrap before baking.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 20 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Enjoy!

title: unique salmon
directions: Pour juice off salmon.
Set aside.
Use fork to mix salmon and egg well.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Mix 1/4 of salmon juice with baking powder.
Beat with fork.
(This will foam; if doesn't, baking powder is old.)
Blend into salmon mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep fryer 1/2 full of oil. Meat is
done when it rises to the top.
Drain on paper towels.

title: microwave tortellini casserole
directions: Chill homemade soup, stew, chili, etc.
Skim the fat from the top and discard.
Reheat the mixture, now with many less calories.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and lightly flour a plain tube pan.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat batter 3 minutes at medium speed and pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in large skillet.
Cook spinach using package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid; add water to make 1 cup.
Add spinach liquid and next 5 ingredients to meat mixture. Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach with macaroni and remaining ingredients; spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamy carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sour cream when warm.
Stir until blended.
Cool until slightly thickened and add remaining ingredients.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juice in buttered cake pan.
Sprinkle with dry Jell-O and dry cake mix.
Pat until smooth.
Pour water over mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Dip into egg, then bread crumbs. Fry in oil on both sides until golden brown.
Remove and place on paper towels.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk, well beaten eggs and shortening.
Bake in greased pan 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently. Add eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Blend in whipping cream. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. (Center will be soft but will set upon cooling.)
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with cherry pie filling.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, large enough to lift out. Separate graham cracker cookies and place on foil.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Melt margarine (oleo) in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir constantly until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat.
Add food coloring; stir well.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Blend flour, soda and cocoa in a bowl.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, melt margarine over low heat and stir in sugar. Remove from heat. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Stir in mixture from bowl. Bake in 2 greased layer pans for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Allow to cool before frosting. (Use Lite Cocoa Frosting.)

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Combine and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: mom's potato rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, potato, 2 cups flour and scalded milk. Add beaten eggs, salt and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix well; let rise 2 hours.
Add 6 cups flour (or enough to make a stiff batter); let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Make into rolls; let rise 1 1/2 hours more.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
I use a heavy aluminum pan.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until everything is thoroughly mixed and melted. Cool and cut.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 2 cups milk (not 4).
Blend in sour cream, bananas and cream.
Cool and serve.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water until a soft ball is formed or until syrup holds shape when dropped in cold water.
Pour syrup into stiffly beaten egg whites and beat until mixture is too stiff to handle with ease.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour on a well-greased platter.

title: cream puffs
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and salt.
Stir well.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating with wooden spoon until smooth. Drop batter by heaping tablespoon 3-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until golden brown and puffy. Cool.
Split open and remove any soft dough inside.
Fill with pudding, whipped cream or fruit.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: lime punch
directions: Add ice milk or sherbet to taste.
Serves 25.

title: no sugar cracker jacks
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, mix together the honey and canola oil.
Heat it over a low heat until it is blended together.
Stir it occasionally.
Place the popped corn and the peanuts in a large bowl and mix them together.
Slowly pour the honey mixture over the popped corn and nuts, stirring as you pour. Spread the mixture out in a single layer on a greased cookie sheet. Bake until they turn a golden brown.
Cool them in a large bowl and store them in an airtight container.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Change water several times, if possible. Cook beans on stove 1 hour. Drain beans. Divide all ingredients between 2 two-quart baking bowls. Add additional brown sugar if you like sweeter beans. Add catsup and water to cover beans. Bake beans, uncovered, 4 to 6 hours at 350°. Check each hour to add water and stir beans if necessary (don't allow beans to dry out).

title: cream-style corn biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick
and corn.
Turn out onto Bisquick-floured board. Pat
to
1/2-inch
thickness.
Cut	into
cookie cutter shapes. Paint with	butter	or margarine. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Thaw strawberries. Drain liquid into a measuring cup. Add enough water to make
1 1/2 c. liquid. Add 2 drops of red coloring.
In a sauce pan mix cornstarch, liquid, sugar and salt. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly till thick.

title: paul's red beans
directions: Brown sausage in black iron pot. Remove sausage. Saute onion in sausage drippings. Add garlic and saute 3 minutes.
Add red beans, all seasonings and water. Simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked rice.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, starting with the butter and ending with the vanilla, in the order given; mix well.
Pour in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with whipped cream. Top with sprinkled coconut, if desired.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Roll wafers into crumbs. Save some to garnish top.
Mix crumbs with butter to form crust.

Melt marshmallows with half and half in top of double boiler. Cool, then add creme de menthe and salt. Fold this into the whipped cream. Pour into crust and freeze. Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and green peas
directions: Cook onions in fat until tender.
Stir in salt and flour. Slowly add broth.
Stir until thick.
Add chicken and peas.
Heat and pour into heated 2 quart shallow casserole dish.
Heat in oven until bubbly and add biscuit topping.
Bake until biscuit topping is done.
By heating the mixture until bubbly and then adding biscuits, they will not be soggy on bottom.

title: blender quiche
directions: Put in blender the milk, eggs, Bisquick, pepper and melted margarine.
Blend the daylights out of it.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan sprayed with Pam.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions and drain. Add to chicken in a large bowl.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine and add to mixture.
Melt cheese and add to other ingredients, stirring well.
Last, add Ro-Tel tomatoes and peas. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Freezes well.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add to soup, let cool.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise, add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold on bed of lettuce.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a kettle, fry bacon, reserving enough fat to saut onion, pepper and potatoes. When onion is translucent, add water and bring to a boil. Add corn, milk, butter and seasonings. Lower heat and simmer until corn is tender, about 10 minutes. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes (recommend blender).
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese in a microwave-safe bowl.
Heat through in microwave. Serve hot with chips.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and remove stems, if desired.
May slice mushrooms or leave whole.
Place on towel and let dry.
Heat frying pan on high.
In hot frying pan, add 1 tablespoon of margarine and pour in onions.
Cook until they begin to show gloss.
Add garlic and stir.
Add remaining margarine.
Add mushrooms.
Saute on high until liquid has evaporated.
Add white wine or brandy and cook until absorbed.

title: south of the border cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease a 10 inch iron skillet. Combine all ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Pour into skillet.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately.

title: terry's peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended, then eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
If necessary, chill dough for 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: baked seafood and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute celery, pepper and onions.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until seafood is cooked.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry dessert bars
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure and set aside 1/2 cup cookie dough.
Pat remainder of dough in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon pie filling over dough.
Break off small pieces of remaining dough and scatter over filling.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 dessert bars.

title: "pastichio me crema salsa" - macaroni and meat casserole
directions: Saute onion in a little water in a large frying pan; add ground beef and brown.
(Pour off excess grease, if any.)
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and dash of cinnamon.
Dissolve tomato paste in the 1/2 cup water, then add to hamburger mixture.
Lower flame and simmer for about 15 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Set aside.
In another large saucepan, put water and 2 teaspoons salt; bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and boil for about 10 minutes or until done.
While macaroni is boiling, combine 1/2 cup milk, 1/4 cup butter, 3/4 cup of the Romano cheese, 1 tablespoon flour and the beaten eggs.
When macaroni is cooked, drain and put back in saucepan and add mixture.
Toss lightly; put aside.
Make Crema.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 1 cup.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: kalee's favorite dinner(very quick and easy)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic.
Add soup and drained green beans.
Put in casserole dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, just to brown top of potatoes and melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over very low heat.
Cool.
Stir butter in mixer bowl to soften. Add flour mixture, 3/4 cup buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add melted chocolate, eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour batter into three 8-inch layer pans lined on the bottom with paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks. Spread filling on layers and stack.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Stir cottage cheese and sour cream together; add macaroni.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Put a layer of sharp Cheddar cheese on top.
Layer with macaroni mixture and another layer of cheese.
Pour milk over top.

title: cauliflower and lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce, cauliflower and onion in large salad bowl.
Add bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese in small bowl.
Add salad just before serving.
As an option, 1 can of ripe olives can be added.

title: tagliarini
directions: Heat olive oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese; cook, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes.
Remove lid from skillet; cook another 10 to 15 minutes.
If Parmesan cheese is used, remove to serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.
If Cheddar cheese is used, fold carefully into mixture.
Serve.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil; beat or mix until light in color.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Bake in loaf pan, one hour at 325°.

title: crock cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add mayonnaise, grated cheese and horseradish.
Stir until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce to taste and garlic salt.
Store in refrigerator.

title: thai pineapple punch
directions: Boil 1 cup water and sugar until a thick syrup is formed. Strain.
Set aside to cool.
Using a pineapple cutter, cut each pineapple into the shape of a bowl.
Chop pineapple pulp into fine pieces. Pour over the hot water.
Squeeze pineapple pulp.
Strain juice.

title: easy "no knead" yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water; set aside.
Scald milk, sugar, salt and oil.
Let cool.
Mix yeast mixture and cooled milk mixture.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Cover, let rise double in bowl, about 45 minutes.
After rising, stir dough a half minute.
Place dough in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover, let rise double in size, 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Brush with oleo.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sour cream.
Slowly add sugar.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time while mixing.
Add cake flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites (beaten stiff).
Bake at 325° in a tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes or bake in 2 loaf pans for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until ice is crushed. Makes five 8-ounce servings.

title: our antipasto buffet
directions: Line a very large platter with lettuce leaves.
Roll salami and place, point side down, in a group on lettuce platter. Arrange all other ingredients in groups on platter.
Pass dressing separately (recipe to follow).

title: cherry tarts
directions: Place vanilla wafer in a cupcake liner.
Beat all other ingredients together.
Add filling mixture until 2/3 full in pans and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
When ready to serve, add canned cherry pie filling on top.
Makes about 18 tarts.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Wash and wipe dry.
Brown in 1/2 cup hot oil over medium heat and set aside until needed. Saute onions in remaining oil until soft.
Add catsup, vinegar, capers, brown sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Now add the chicken into the mixture.
Add water until the sauce is even with the chicken.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cake mix spritz
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place mixture into cookie press; pipe onto baking sheet.	Bake at 350° until done.
Watch carefully.

title: shrimp-rice skillet casserole
directions: Cook
bacon in 10-inch skillet until crisp.
Remove and drain on
paper
towel.
Drain
off
all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from skillet.
Combine broth and vinegar in 1 quart bowl.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, onion and tarragon
or celery
seed.
Cover
tightly and cook on low 45 minutes.
Remove cover
and
stir in green pepper and shrimp. Cover
and cook until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Stir
in
bacon
and jalapeno
or
pimento.
Preparation
and cooking time:
1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cook meat overnight on low in crock-pot.
Debone and pull meat apart. Put meat back in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce. Cook on low for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: roast chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat
12-inch Dutch oven.
Pour oil into Dutch oven and heat 5
minutes.
Add garlic, potatoes and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stir.
Bake	10 minutes.
Rub chickens inside and out with salt and rosemary.	Put 1 bay leaf and lemon in each chicken.
Put vegetables to one side and place chickens in the middle of	the oven and bake for 2 1/2 hours.
Cook on medium heat.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk, crush with hands until well mixed.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins; stir well.
Pour oleo in bottom of thick pan and bake until very firm.
Let cool.
Cube pudding and put in individual dessert dish.
When ready to serve, add sauce and heat broiler.

title: jane's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil, debone, skin and cut chicken into bite size pieces; reserve broth.
Parboil in chicken broth the vegetables with parsley, oregano, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add chicken, cut up; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
This should fill pan to depth of about 1 1/2 inches.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meats and drain well.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Put on party rye bread slices and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and mashed bananas.
Sift together and blend the flour, soda and salt.
Add these slowly to banana mixture.
Add sour cream, vanilla, nuts and cinnamon.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 lightly-greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut breasts into strips.
Marinate strips in 1 cup water and the fajitas seasoning mix for 2 hours.
Heat oil in heavy saucepan and saute onion and red and green peppers until tender-crisp. Remove vegetables from pan and add chicken strips, reserving marinade.
Saute chicken until light brown.
Add leftover marinade and simmer for 5 minutes.
Return vegetables to pan and heat to mingle flavors.
Spoon mixture into warm tortillas.
Fold over and garnish with sour cream, salsa, guacamole and slice of lime.

title: turkey divan quiche
directions: Arrange turkey and broccoli in unbaked pie shell.
Toss cheese with flour, salt, cayenne and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over turkey and broccoli.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over filling. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: topping or dip for fruit
directions: Mix well together and enjoy.

title: joanne's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually mix in moist ingredients.
Mix dry and moist ingredients together until evenly blended.
Pour into 4 oiled 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well.
Grease cookie sheet and cover with wax paper.
Spread batter on pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place dish towel on table and sprinkle powdered sugar all over towel.
When cake is done, place on towel and peel off wax paper.
Roll cake up like jelly roll inside towel.
Chill.

title: dresdener stollen(christmas yeast bread of dresden)
directions: Soak the fruit in rum while preparing the dough.
Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar and butter.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and butter melted.
Cool to lukewarm milk mixture and the eggs.
Stir to blend, then beat until smooth and dough easily comes away from bowl.
Drain the fruit; add with lemon rind 1/4 cup of the almonds to the 3/4 cup flour.
Toss until fruit and nuts are well coated.
Add coated fruit and nuts to the dough. Work with fingers until all nuts are well distributed in the dough. Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
If too sticky, work in a little more flour.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: ham pie
directions: Put ham in a saucepan with water; boil to tender.
Make a crust.
Line pan with parts of crust.
Put 1/2 meat in the pan and add pieces of crust and butter.
Add juice of meat and the rest of meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Place in plate and take fork and punch holes in cake.
Put strawberry juice on.
Spread Cool Whip all over cake.
Put strawberries on top.
Put on another top part. Punch holes.
Add strawberry juice, Cool Whip and strawberries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: reeses peanut butter cups
directions: Combine and spread first 4 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: apple jolly rancher
directions: Mix well. Serve on ice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate the cherry tomatoes, black olives and broccoli in Italian dressing for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook the fettucini noodles; drain, then refrigerate for approximately 1 hour.
Combine the marinated ingredients with the noodles.
Mix and add Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Serve.

title: frito casserole
directions: Put 1 can of beans in casserole dish.
Spread half of the chili on top of the beans.
Add half of cheese slices next and a layer of Fritos corn chips.
Repeat all the layers again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles around edge.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place peppers in microwavable dish, cut side down and cook on High, uncovered, for 4 minutes. Turn over. In mixing bowl, combine next 3 ingredients and mix well. Mix together diced tomatoes, ketchup and Tabasco sauce. Then add 1/4 cup of this to the ground beef, onion and brown rice mixture. Divide beef-rice-tomato mixture evenly among green pepper halves. Then spoon remaining diced tomato mixture over top. Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, until beef mixture is 160°.

title: easy rice and peas
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water, butter and salt to a boil. Add rice and peas; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix; do not roll out.
Cover dough and set aside.

title: sara's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit for 5 minutes, if possible.
Cook on griddle until golden brown on each side.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together taco mix, taco sauce, sour cream and mayonnaise; put tomatoes, onions and cheese on top.
Use dip size corn chips.

title: italian spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Form meat into 1-inch balls.
Combine ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drop in meatballs.
Cover and cook about an hour. Cook spaghetti just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato cheese hash
directions: Make the Night Before: Mix all but Parmesan cheese together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with Parmesan cheese and cover. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand until cool, about 20 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add well beaten eggs.
Stir in oatmeal.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla; mix well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix together
and
bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook slowly (about 1
hour
or until thick).
Put in jars and seal. These ingredients may be pureed in blender.

title: summer delight cake
directions: Mix well, beating 5 minutes and bake in 3 layers in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Heat until cheese melts.
Take off heat and whip until smooth. Add pepper, onion, pecans and mayo.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
In large Dutch oven or kettle, add all ingredients, except rice and bring to a boil, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Reduce heat to low and cook slowly for several hours.
If necessary, add water if beans are not tender.
If you want thicker gravy, mash a few beans and cook until remaining beans are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: orange cake
directions: Add to beaten egg whites.
Pour over cake.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Frost with whipped cream.
Put one layer on plate; pour some of the orange juice over, then put other layer right on top of first and pour rest of juice over.
There is no filling in the middle.

title: cherry tomatoes stuffed with blue cheese
directions: With a small melon ball cutter, scoop out the cherry tomato pulp.
Sprinkle the shells with salt.
Invert them on a rack and let them drain for 15 minutes.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, crumbled Blue cheese, grated onion and salt and pepper to taste. Fill tomatoes with the mixture and sprinkle with chopped chives.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add vanilla and dry ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir milk and soup together.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer potatoes, onion and soup.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes more.
This is easy and it never fails!

title: garlic butter
directions: In a mortar and pestle, crush 2 or 3 cloves of peeled garlic. (The broad side of a knife hit against the clove makes it easier to peel.)
Add a few drops of oil.
Add 1 or 2 more cloves of garlic while continuing to crush the mixture in the mortar.
Your finished consistency should by silky.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Add beans and simmer.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes, avocado and onion.
Mix.
When ready to serve, add crumbled chips, cheese, meat and dressing.

title: apple fritter rings
directions: In a bowl, beat egg, milk, and oil.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Stir into the egg mixture until smooth, batter will be thick.
Peel, core, and cut apples into 1/2 inch rings.
In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Dip apple rings into batter.
Fry a few at a time, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over hot fritters.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for a day.

title: carol's italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Beat and add buttermilk, soda, flour, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch layers.

title: more casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Save 1 cup cheese. Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Add the 1 cup of cheese on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover sides and bottom of pan with 13 biscuits rolled out. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Roll out the other 7 biscuits. Cut into strips and put on top of ingredients. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 1 hour.
Jar and seal.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix in favorite punch bowl.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Crush 24 to 26 cookies.
Melt margarine and add to cookie crumbs.
Pat into pie pan; save some for top of pie.

title: sweet and sour beans(very good)
directions: Cook in moderate oven until most of juice is absorbed, 2 to 3 hours.

title: microwave nacho cheese dip
directions: Combine in microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once after 2 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: fruit dip i
directions: Mix the ingredients together and serve with orange slices, apple slices, strawberries, bananas, melons, etc.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate morsels in double boiler. Meanwhile, beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add melted mixture to this.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into two deep-dish unbaked pie shells (Deep Dish).
Bake for 30 or 40 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Top with crackers and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first two ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of the mixture for the topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to the reserved topping mix.
Mix the reserved topping well and set aside.
Press the remaining mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange the apple slices over the base.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake in a large casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
May add chopped chicken, if desired.

title: $25,000 mexican dish
directions: Mix Bisquick, water, and beans; spread in greased 9x13 pan. Sprinkle fried hamburger on top.
Spread salsa and shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350°F for 30 min. Top with sour cream, lettuce, and tomatoes just before serving.
Delicious!

title: cheesy corn chowder
directions: In large glass bowl, combine ham, red pepper, onion and butter. Cover bowl with vented plastic wrap.
In microwave, cook on High 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and corn. Cook, uncovered, on High 10 minutes or until hot.
Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for garnish.
In small bowl, combine remaining cheese, cornstarch, salt and ground red pepper.
Stir cheese mixture into soup.
Cook, uncovered, on High 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in cilantro; spoon into individual serving bowls.
Sprinkle reserved 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
