Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Pour dressing mix over the ingredients and let sit for 1 hour before serving.
Mix well.
This is a good dish.

title: stir-fry
directions: Start with your meat.
Fry until brown.
Put in carrots, potatoes and broccoli until lightly softened, then add onions, peppers, mushrooms, tomatoes and all spices and meat stock. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg in mixer bowl; beat well. Press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl; beat well.
Spread over cake mix layer.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
In a medium saucepan, cook meat, onion, carrot and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water, basil, oregano, fennel, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Meanwhile cook noodles according to directions and drain.

title: granola
directions: Making Baking Powder:
When I'm out of baking powder, I make my own.
Sift together 2 tablespoons cream of tartar, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon baking soda.

title: moravian scotch cakes
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and caraway seed together.
Cut in the butter with a pastry blender or two knives until well blended. Roll out about 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut into small squares.
Transfer to greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
When cooled, spread with boiled icing and sprinkle with sugar.

title: yeast or angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add 1 cup buttermilk to this and yeast. Add other cup buttermilk.
Knead.
Refrigerate as long as you desire.
Cut with biscuit cutter and dip in melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix all ingredients; pour milk in slowly.
Pour and mix until you have a moist (but not wet) mixture.
These biscuits are best in the mini muffin pans. Spray pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until tops are slightly brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving small amount of liquid. Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in salmon, cornmeal and other ingredients. Shape into patties. Use small amount of oil in skillet and fry patties until browned.

title: stephanie's cabbage rolls
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onions, salt and pepper. Combine rice, hamburger and 3 cans of tomato soup. Steam cabbage so layers "fall" apart. Put 2 Tbsp. or more (don't overfill) of mixture in a cabbage leaf. Roll cabbage leaf and layer closely in a large casserole dish or roasting pan. Top each layer with remaining cans of tomato soup. Cook slowly for 3-3 1/2 hours at 325-350°. Watch closely so that it does not boil over, and marinate as you go.

title: spanish gunk
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve with tortillas or chips, lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, onion, cheese, ripe olives, salsa or sour cream.
This is a crowd pleaser!

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until very soft.
Cut potatoes lengthwise and scoop out insides.
Whip potatoes.
Add sour cream, grated onion and shredded cheese. Refill potato skins.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 375° until top is golden, for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate amaretto balls
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Amaretto and extract.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll in nuts.
Chill until firm.
Store at room temperature in tightly covered container. (Flavor improves after 24 hours.)

title: southern-fried chicken
directions: Mix cornmeal, both peppers and salt.
Coat catfish with flour. Dip into eggs, then coat with cornmeal mixture.
Fry in 1/2-inch very hot oil about 6 minutes one each side.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add tomato paste and seasonings, then combine with string beans.
Place in casserole. Cover with mashed potatoes and grated cheese to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: yankee tacos
directions: Brown meat and onions; add to beans.
Add catsup, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly and add cheese until melted.
Serve with or on tortillas.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli in salted water; drain.
Place on top of chicken.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour.
Add cheese and broth and cook until thick.
Add whipping cream; stir until smooth.
Put over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together meat, crumbs, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Baste often with vinegar, water, brown sugar and mustard mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: martha faye zelinski's family jello
directions: *Note:
Be sure to use 8 ounces of Coke, not a 12 ounce can of Coke.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: chocolate covered fondant
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together (mix like bread dough).
Add last 3 ingredients.
Form into balls.
Let stand on wax paper until firm in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up broccoli and cook in microwave for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Melt margarine.
Add rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and onion.
Add cooked broccoli.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Cook corn syrup and sugar until mixture thickens.
Beat eggs well, add hot syrup slowly while continuing to beat.
Add the melted butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then lower oven to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes.
Cool and serve with or without whipped topping.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Mixing well, combine eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Make a well in middle of dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry mixture.
Fill one 6 x 6 x 2-inch foil pan or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (for large pan, 60 minutes).

title: lula bell special peach dessert
directions: Put grated coconut in each peach half; turn upside down in pie crust.
Beat egg yolks and mix with instant pudding.
Sprinkle coconut over peaches, then put pudding over all.
Beat egg whites with sugar.
Put over pie.
Bake pie under broiler until brown.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter top of bread and layer bread, cheese and meat.
Repeat.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread mixture and refrigerate.
Prepare the night before serving.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as direct on package.
Rinse with cold water to cool.
Add olives, pimentos, carrot, broccoli and onion.
Stir. Follow directions on dressing using olive oil and vinegar.
Add to pasta and stir.
Garnish with pepperoni on top.

title: fettuccine with prosciutto and vegetables(4 servings)
directions: In medium skillet over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Add Prosciutto, scallions and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add carrots, zucchini, peas and broth; bring to a boil.
Lower heat to medium; simmer 5 minutes.
Place fettuccine in large serving bowl.
Spoon vegetable mixture over fettuccine. Add tomato, Parmesan cheese and pepper to taste; toss to mix well. Contains 153 calories per serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well. Spoon in a graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Soften butter; mix eggs, sugars and milk until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add other ingredients.
Stir.
Place by tablespoon on cookie sheets.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: jell-o balls
directions: Mix 2 boxes of Jell-O and the milk, then add vanilla and coconut.
Mix until slightly thickened.
Pour other 2 boxes of dry Jell-O into a plate.
Make small balls from mixture and then roll them in dry Jell-O.

title: mimi's oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream brown sugar, shortening (Crisco) and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar and shortening mixture.
Then add oats and chopped walnuts. Mix well.
Form into long roll; chill thoroughly (wrap in foil or plastic wrap to keep from drying out). Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt at 350° in oven in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish the margarine.
Layer with ingredients as listed.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool completely.
Cut in small bars.

title: portobello pecan stuffing
directions: Put butter and oil in an extra-deep nonstick skillet; heat at medium-high. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 1 minute. Add garlic and chopped Portobello and button mushrooms; cook, stirring frequently, until the mushrooms have released their liquid, about 2 minutes. Add the amount of water called for on the stuffing package. Add the seasoning packet from the stuffing package. Bring the mixture to a boil. Stir in the stuffing crumbs. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: With water (1 1/2 cups), simmer bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and celery until tender.
Chop garlic; add to pan.
Add spices. Now add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Stir all together.
Put over pasta.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch cake pan with Pam.
Pour in cherry pie filling.
Spread evenly in pan.
Empty cake mix on top of filling and spread evenly. Dot the top of cake with margarine slices (plentiful).
Bake at 375° until light golden brown, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy tuna salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in blender container; allow to stand while assembling other ingredients.
Add boiling water, cover and process at low speed until gelatin dissolves.
Add bouillon cubes with remaining ingredients.
Cover and process at high speed just until vegetables are chopped.
Turn into 3 or 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mrs. meacham's 6 week bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal, buttermilk, oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into cereal mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours before using.
To bake, fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
If batter is kept covered, it should keep for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 dozen muffins.

title: fast german chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread coconut and chopped pecans over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as instructed on box. Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Soften butter and cream cheese.
Mix with sugar and pour over mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese; put only part of cheese in mix.
Save most to put on top.
Bake at 370° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: hungarian frittata
directions: Cut sausages into strips and salami into slices.
Rinse peppers, remove seeds and cut into slices.
Rinse and slice tomatoes.
Peel and slice onions.
Saute sausages and salami in a skillet for 3 minutes.
Add onion and peppers.
Saute a few minutes longer.
Add tomatoes and reduce heat.
Beat eggs.
Put all ingredients into a pan and pour eggs over all.
Stir mixture over medium heat until eggs set.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with rye bread or old-fashioned wheat bread.

title: pizza dough
directions: Blend flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Add hot water (120°) and oil.
Mix together.
Dough may be sticky.
Add a little flour in order to handle.
Shape to fit pan.
Add your toppings!
Cook at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Then add eggs, milk, flavoring and flour.
Beat at least 10 minutes on medium speed.
Batter will be thick in texture.
Dip into pan with a spoon.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 250°.
Grease and flour pan.
Makes an extra large cake.

title: apple oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400° and line 12 muffin pan cups.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl and add flour mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Spoon batter into cups almost to the top of each tin.
Bake 25 minutes or until firm.
Cool in wire rack.
Serves 12.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni and drain. Combine macaroni and next 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Mix well. Sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shirley's easy lime pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine limeade (undiluted) and sweetened condensed milk. Add sour cream; stir until well blended. Fold in the prepared whipped topping. Add food coloring as desired. Mixture should be thick and mound when dropped from spoon. (If mixture seems thin, chill for 30 minutes.) Spoon into crust. Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Garnish. Makes 1 pie.

title: 7-up applesauce jello mold
directions: Put applesauce in saucepan with jello.
Bring to boil.
Shut off heat and cool 30 minutes.
Add 7-Up.
Put mixture in mold or in tray for slices.
Great with pork or ham.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 7 ingredients together, stirring to blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes or until firm in center.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grilled salmon
directions: For marinade, combine all ingredients except steaks.
Pour mixture over salmon in a shallow glass baking dish.
Refrigerate, covered, 30 to 60 minutes.
Drain.
Wrap steaks in foil that is lightly buttered.
Cook 20 minutes (depending on thickness of steaks).

title: taco salad(dinner in a bowl)
directions: Use amounts of ingredients to your preference.
In a large bowl add chopped lettuce, chopped tomato, diced onion and shredded cheddar cheese.
Stir together.
Add green taco sauce (about 1/2 bottle) and thousand island dressing.
Stir well.
Add sliced olives, avocado and hamburger (cooked and drained).
Pull open a small hole in the top of the nacho bag.
Crush the chips until they are in small pieces.
Pour into the rest of the ingredients and stir completely.
You may need to adjust the amount of dressing so that your salad is not dry.
Serve immediately.

title: denise's baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large casserole dish. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickle's chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Set aside.
Cut cookie roll in 1/2.
Out of each 1/2, cut 16 slices. Much easier if you work with a very cold roll.
(Don't take out of refrigerator until you're ready to cut.)
Place 16 slices on bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square cake pan.
Add cheese filling; top with remaining 16 slices.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
It's delicious!

title: roasted chicken
directions: Trim all fat from chicken.
Separate skin from flesh by running fingers under skin as far as possible.
Combine onions, bell pepper and garlic in food processor and chop fine.
Stuff this seasoning between skin and flesh as far as possible.
Season the cavity and outside of chicken with salt and pepper.
Cover and let it sit in refrigerator overnight.
Place chicken on rack in roasting pan. Pour 1 cup wine and 1 cup chicken broth over chicken; cover and roast in oven at 325° for about 2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: white peanut butter candy
directions: Soften the butter or margarine.
Mix all the ingredients together until smooth.
Spread into 8-inch pan or plate. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and line baking pan with foil.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a loaf and cover with foil, baking 1 1/2 hours or until done in the center.
Top with onions and green peppers, if desired.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
In slow cooker, place cooked sausage, Velveeta cheese (cut up) and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over chips when ready to serve.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: chicken in the pan
directions: Cut up chicken.
Alternate layers of chicken, onions and mushrooms, finishing with onions on top. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Cover pan and put in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn down the heat to 175° and cook for 8 hours without burning it.
One half hour before serving, put chicken under broiler for 15 minutes to brown top and turn gently under to brown.
Serve with potatoes or noodles.

title: white icing
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add sugar and beat until very light and fluffy.
Mix milk and flour together.
Cook slowly until creamy, stirring constantly. Let set until cold (completely cold), then add to mixture and mix and beat well.

title: autumn soup
directions: Cook and stir the onions with ground beef until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: "finger food"
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers. Place crackers on cookie sheet and pour mixture over them. Let this stand overnight. Store in an airtight container.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil and eggs together at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Add carrots and nuts and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in roasting pan.
Sprinkle sesame seed over butter and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes to brown slightly.
Dip chicken pieces in flour to coat all sides. Put in roasting pan, turning to coat thoroughly in butter.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.
With a slotted spoon, remove chicken to chafing dish or serving bowl.
To pan juices in roasting pan, add green onions, parsley, seasonings and soy sauce.
Place pan over heat and stir, scraping to incorporate residue in pan into sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter with crumbs; sprinkle crumbs over the bottom of baking pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Add dry ingredients to wet and beat until smooth.
Do not grease pan.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and ice in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Press hamburger in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over hamburger.
Add beans and then pour
over
all
with celery soup.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Put foil on tight.
Bake 2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: elegant green beans
directions: Combine soup, onion, oregano, garlic salt and sour cream. Toss with beans.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cream brown sugar, margarine and eggs until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir 1/2 the dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Add pineapple and juice, then remaining dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts and pour into pan.
Mix cinnamon with white sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes.
Slice.
Serve plain or spread with cream cheese for sandwiches.
Freezes well.

title: jackie williams danish bars
directions: Sift flour and salt. Cut in Crisco until crumbly. Add enough milk to egg yolk to make 1/2 cup. Add to flour mixture.
Mix until moist. Divide dough in half. Roll out first half large enough for jelly roll pan (15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Press up on sides of pan. Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes. Arrange fruit over flakes.
Pour sugar over fruit. Roll out the other half of the dough to fit top.
Make vents in top. Seal edges.
Spread egg whites over crust. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden. Combine powdered sugar, water and vanilla to make glaze.
Spread on Danish while warm.

title: goothis was peg catanach's recipe
directions: Brown ground meat with onion.
Salt and pepper, if desired. Add chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, and soup.
Cook until blended.
Cook noodles, drain and put in casserole dish.
Top with ground meat mixture.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Stir in flour and nuts. Bake in a loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Cook until done in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: marzipan cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, food coloring and flavoring.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Shape into fruit.
For most cookies, use 2 level teaspoons of dough to form cookies.
Place cookies on ungreased baking sheet.
Chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 300°.
Bake about 30 minutes, depending on size and thickness.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bring to a boil the juice and grated rind of the lemons with water added to make 2 cups.
Beat the egg yolks, sugar and cornstarch together.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons water to make a mixture to pour into water and juice.
Stir and cook until thick. Add oleo and pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and cool.
Brown ground beef.
To ground beef, add mushrooms and spaghetti sauce and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Put small amount of sauce mixture in bottom of large casserole dish.
Layer 3 noodles, 1/3 of sauce and half of cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese for three layers.
In place of final layer of cheese, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed on package; chill until set.
Stir in marshmallows and whipped topping, just until blended.
In a large bowl, layer the wafers, then the mixture, then layer of bananas, until all is used.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and leave whole if diameter is less than 1 inch. If carrots are large, cut in half lengthwise.
Cook in a pot on top of the stove until tender.
Drain the water and empty the carrots into a casserole dish.

title: conch or clam sauce with linguine
directions: Sauce:	Cook salt pork in skillet until brown and crispy. Remove salt pork scraps and set aside.
Add butter (or margarine) and olive oil to skillet and heat until butter is melted.
Mash garlic and parsley together and add to skillet, cooking slowly until soft.
Add conch or clams and heat through.
Add flour and pepper, stirring well, and cook for 3 minutes.
Slowly add 1 cup clam juice and Tabasco and bring to boil stirring constantly.
Thin the sauce with more clam juice if it becomes too thick; however, be careful not to make it too liquid.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large bowl combine cake mix, oil and eggs; stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in candy bits from cake mix.
Shape dough into one-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
With bottom of glass dipped in flour, flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool one minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Spread frosting over cookies. Immediately sprinkle each with candy bits from frosting.
Allow frosting to set before storing.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in pie pan with fingers. Pour over evaporated milk; don't mix in.
Put butter on top. Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crumbs and pecans; pour in a buttered dish.
Bake 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove from oven and top with crumbs and nuts.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
May also be doubled, if so, use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
You may substitute the following for low calorie:
Egg Beaters, low fat cheese, margarine for butter, plain yogurt for mayonnaise and artificial sweetener.

title: sweet and sour short ribs
directions: Brown ribs in skillet to remove fat and place in slow cooker (crock-pot).
Add all the other ingredients and stir well to coat ribs.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Put the onion, celery and bell pepper in a heavy skillet with oil and cook over a medium heat for 15 minutes; do not brown.
Add salt, red pepper, tomato sauce, liquid and raw shrimp.
Cook for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add raw rice and some chopped parsley if desired.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole; cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until rice is done.
Do not stir or uncover during cooking.

title: gracie's salsa
directions: Put all of these ingredients into a blender to chop it down, but do not overblend it.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil rice in 1 1/2 cups of water.
Use direction on box.
Cook broccoli; add butter to rice. Mix all in 9-inch round casserole. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.

title: english plum pudding
directions: Add milk to bread to moisten.
Mix all together.
Put in large pan and steam for 3 hours.
Any kind of your favorite sauce may be used over this.
Lemon sauce is good.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Pour rice in pan.
Place breasts over top of rice, skin side up (breasts may be skinless).
Mix soup, orange juice and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Pour into buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar with butter and add to egg, vanilla and corn syrup.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat into first mixture. Roll into balls the size of walnuts, then roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together and beat until light and fluffy shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, cream and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour and gradually add to creamed mixture.
On floured board, roll out dough and cut with round cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° until delicately browned.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well; shape into 2 or 3 rolls.
Roll up in aluminum foil (shiny side next to meat).
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a deep clear crystal bowl, arrange in layers.

title: best of the west beans
directions: Cook, scramble and drain hamburg.
Dice onion and add to hamburg.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add hamburg and onion. Simmer until ready to eat.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in juice, oil, egg and vanilla just until blended. Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Turn out onto rack and cool completely.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook stew beef until almost done.
Cut potatoes and carrots into chunks and add to meat.
Cook until tender.
Salt to taste.

title: white salad
directions: Cook pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and flour until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Whip cream and fold into first mixture.
Pour over pineapple and bananas and chill.

title: jane's cheddar crisps
directions: With mixer cream butter and Cheddar cheese and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, little at a time, beating and adding salt and cayenne.
Beat well.
Add cereal and beat until it is just combined.
Form heaping teaspoonfuls into balls.
Arrange 2 inches apart on buttered baking sheet.
Flatten with floured fork. Bake in middle of preheated oven 15 minutes or until golden. Makes about 55 cookies.
Keeps in airtight container 1 week.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Brown meat in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Mix liquids and add 1/2 of this to mixture.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours.
Add rest of liquid during cooking. Just before serving, add sliced pickles.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.
(The pickles make this special.)

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients into a large 4-quart mixing bowl.
Add pecans, pineapple, cherries and raisins.
Mix until all fruit and nuts are well coated with dry ingredients. Set aside.

title: sara ann c. caramels
directions: Mix all together, stirring constantly.
Boil about 35 to 50 minutes and test in cold water.
Pour into a buttered shallow pan. Cool and cut into squares; wrap.

title: alma cookies
directions: Mix with wet hands.
Form into balls, hollow out the centers and bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out of oven and fill centers with your favorite jelly or jam; bake 5 minutes more. Remove from oven; cool.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Drain vegetables, except tomatoes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix everything together in large bowl and stir.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and a drop of cold water.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Store while still warm in a closed container.

title: cumberland mountain pie(about 150 years old)
directions: Line a pie tin with pastry.
Prick with a fork.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Take out.
Pour in fillings and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: triscuit toppers
directions: Pour jalapeno tomatoes into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square or 1-quart casserole.
Mix milk, egg and cheese.
Pour over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all together and divide.
This will roll out into 3 crusts.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Sift flour with salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine meal.
Sprinkle with warer, a tablespoon at a time mixing lightly with fork until all the flour is moistened.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Combine the cream cheese and brown sugar.
Form into a ball; chill.
Pour caramel topping over cream cheese.
Slice apple wedges into lemon juice and water to avoid browning.
Drain apples on paper towels.
Place on serving plate around cheese ball that has been topped with caramel.

title: baked pork chops with onion gravy
directions: Brown chops quickly in hot skillet; place in 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion in margarine and pan drippings until brown.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Add milk, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Bake covered at 300° for 2 hours or until tender, stirring twice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: surkal(sweet and sour red cabbage)
directions: Remove core from cabbage and cut into fine strips.
Put oleo in pan.
Layer cabbage and apples with flour, caraway seed and salt.
Pour cold liquid over. Boil over low heat while tightly covered. Stir now and then. Add more water if necessary. Season to taste with vinegar and sugar.
Approximate cooking time, 1 to 2 hours.

title: quick peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in heavy iron skillet.
Bring the mixture to a boil at low to medium heat.
Add peanuts and boil until syrup is light tan, about 6 minutes from time it begins to boil after the nuts are added.
Remove from heat and add the baking soda.
Stir briskly and quickly.
Spread out on a cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add coconut, fruits, carrots and nuts.
In separate bowl, whisk eggs with oil and vanilla.
Pour mixture into bowl of dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4ths full.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; turn out onto rack.
Best if allowed to ripen for 24 hours. Freezes well.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon slices.
Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12 x
2-inch baking dish with beef.
Place breasts on top.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: diabetic farmers salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce in a mixing bowl and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: chopped broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze excess water from thawed broccoli and drain well.
Place broccoli in a large bowl; mix in mushroom soup, grated cheese, mayonnaise, egg, onion and cayenne pepper, if desired.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart casserole that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: pretty potatoes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, paprika, relish, parsley, onion and garlic salt.
Put in a covered jar and refrigerate several hours.
Wash and boil potatoes until tender.
Place hot boiled potatoes in a dish.
Put whipped oleo on top (cut in pieces). Pour mayonnaise mixture over this.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.
Great with steak.

title: m&m super cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Add 1 1/2 cups M&M's; drop by rounded spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Immediately press 3 candies into top of each cookie.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute before removing.

title: leo's favorite date cookies
directions: Stir
up the night before.
Mix in order given then put into a
bowl and cover.
In the morning, heat oven to 325° to 350°. Drop
by
teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake for 20
to
25 minutes.
Makes several dozen according to size of cookie dough used.
Keeps well.

title: thick spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat has browned.
Drain off drippings. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: chicken 'n' gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large Reynolds oven bag. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in bag.
Place carrots and celery around chicken.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake about 45 to 50 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cake special
directions: Stir vinegar and milk together and set aside.
Cream the shortening and add sugar, eggs and dry ingredients, alternating in 3 to 4 stages with the sour milk.
Stir in the hot water and vanilla.

Bake in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan or two 9-inch round pans or three 8-inch round pans for 35 to 45 minutes (approximately, it will vary according to the size of the pan and the heating quirks of the particular oven) at 350°.
The pans should be lined with paper and greased.

title: royal coconut cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a bowl. Add sugars, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Chill several hours, then shape into 1 inch balls, using a melon baller.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fruit cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs first.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Soak for 2 days or more with grape juice or wine.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits into quarters, dip into sugar and cinnamon mixture and put into tube pan.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: karo-nut pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add flour to sugar, then add to egg mixture. Add buttermilk, syrup, salt and vanilla. Cut butter into small pieces and add to mixture; beat well. (A wire egg beater is better than an electric mixer.) Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until top is slightly brown. Reduce oven temperature to 250° and bake 45 minutes or until set.

title: ham apple casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat together milk and egg; add to rest of ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until topping is browned.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Toast bread lightly.
Arrange slices of turkey on the toast. Spread sauerkraut over turkey and top with cheese.
Bake at 450° or put under broiler until the sandwich is thoroughly heated and the cheese is melted.
Garnish with watercress, dill pickle and radish rose.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Boil the margarine, cocoa and water together.
Pour boiled mixture over top of remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in 11 x 14 pan 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: helen's clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and break into small pieces.
Cook 1 onion in small amount of bacon fat until browned.
Add water, tomatoes and celery.
Simmer a while with Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire. Then add clams and potatoes and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bake at 325 degrees for 10 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled pretzel layer.
Mix last 2 ingredients together and jell a little.
Then spread on above layer.
Refrigerate then serve.

title: quick snacking crackers
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Toss with crackers.
Let stand for several hours, stirring occasionally.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour and pecans.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape in balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and sift confectioners sugar on cookies. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook the whole chicken breasts; chop up.
Mix the stuffing mix with a little celery, onion and parsley.
Mix both chicken and stuffing mixture with the Miracle Whip.
Cook the macaroni al dente.
Stuff shells and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the soup with the water; pour over stuffed shells.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes about 36 shells.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop up dried beef and sprinkle over the pan.
Take chicken breasts and wrap each one with 1 strip of bacon.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 2 hours.

title: pecan rice
directions: Spray the inside of a small skillet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray and place over high heat.
Add the onions, celery and pecan meal; saute, stirring, for 3 minutes, then remove from the heat and set aside.

title: ham loaf
directions: Spread catsup over top of loaf.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare mix as directed on box.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup of Carnation milk.
Mix with butter in saucepan.
Low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over the cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips, then pour other half of cake mix over this.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut the tips off the wings and reserve for another use such as stock.
Halve the wings at the joint.
In a large deep fryer or large deep kettle, heat 2-inches of oil to 380°.
Fry the wings, patted dry, in small batches, for 5 to 8 minutes, or until they are golden and crisp.
Transfer with tongs to paper towels to drain. Make sure oil is heated to 380° before frying next batch.
In a large skillet, melt the butter with the Tabasco, the vinegar and salt to taste over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add the wings and heat them, tossing to coat with the mixture.
Serve the wings warm, or at room temperature, with the Blue Cheese Dressing and the celery sticks.

title: oven crisp chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, mix together sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Place stuffing mix in a blender or food processor; process until it resembles fine crumbs.
Coat the chicken pieces with the sour cream mixture, then roll in the crumbs.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: canadian muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°; put rack in middle of oven.
Dark pans may require slightly lower temperature or shorter baking time than shiny pans.
Grease muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.

title: j.f.k. irish bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; cut in butter.
Stir in sugar and raisins.
Combine milk and eggs; beat with hand beater. Mix with flour, etc., and stir well.
Put in loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special fruitcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine nuts, dates and cherries.
In another bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add to nut mixture, stirring until nuts and fruit are well coated. Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in vanilla; fold into nut mixture. Mix well.
Pour into a greased and waxed paper-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well; pat on paper towel.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Or serve in hollowed out round loaf of bread.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, except salt.
Heat until cheese melts and is smooth.
Stir occasionally.
Season with salt. Serve in a chafing dish.

title: jeanette and dick's wedding punch
directions: All juices should be chilled in refrigerator.
Combine all ingredients, making sure sugar is completely dissolved.
Makes approximately 50 (6 ounce) cups.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Soak the bread in the scalded milk for 5 minutes.
Add to this (after the 5 minutes soak) the salt, butter or margarine and sugar.
Pour the mixture slowly over the eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a large, greased baking dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in covered container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup with boiling water.

title: french scrambled eggs
directions: In a large, deep bowl, lightly whisk eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mash the cream cheese with parsley and dill until well blended.
In a large skillet (nonstick) heat butter until it's sizzling, but not brown.
Pour in egg mixture and over low heat, gently stir the eggs until they just begin to thicken.
Immediately add the herbed cream cheese in several chunks and stir constantly until the eggs are set and creamy. Serves 6.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in a glass bowl in a microwave.
Add milk and pudding mix.
Cook for 1 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and sweetener.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix by hand.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks. Bake in muffin pans for 30-35 minutes at 350°.

title: donnie's mexican tortillas
directions: In mixer or blender, beat eggs at medium speed.
Gradually add dry ingredients; alternate with milk and oil.
Beat until smooth. Spoon mixture about the size of pancakes onto hot griddle and lightly brown, about 30 seconds.
Remove from griddle.
In frying pan, fry hamburger; drain and add 1 can Sloppy Joe mix.
Take tortillas and Sloppy Joe mix, shredded cheese, lettuce, sour cream, hot sauce, onions, olives or anything you want to add. Fold tortillas in half.

title: fried rice (oriental)
directions: Prepare rice according to box instructions.
To the finished rice mix, add the brown sugar, soy sauce, chopped green onions and egg.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandmother's baked beans
directions: Wash the beans and let soak in warm water overnight.
Simmer the beans until about half-done.
Fry the diced onions in bacon grease until clear.
Add the tomato puree to the onions and cook for about 10 minutes.
Pour the onion mixture into the beans and cook until done.
Pour the beans after discarding slab of meat into an oblong baking dish.
Cover the top of the beans with slices of bacon.
Pepper and brown in the oven until the bacon is done.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Beat Crisco and 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add flour and mix. Cool.
Divide dough in 4 balls.
Roll out to fill with apples. Combine 3/4 cup sugar with 1/2 kettle full water.
Simmer (a lite syrup).
Combine apples, cinnamon and sweeten to taste.
Mix well. Put apples on rolled out dough.
Roll and make sure the apple ball is closed good.
Drop in syrup and cook very slow (simmer) one or two at a time.
Repeat until all are cooked and are nice and brown. These are great plain or with vanilla ice cream of milk.
These can be baked in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut back on syrup if baked.

title: chicken and chinese noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 of noodles for topping. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with remaining noodles and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: herbed potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into cubes and place in a large bowl.
Add celery and remaining ingredients; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine together.
Crush graham crackers in blender.
Add all ingredients to melted marshmallows and margarine.
When mixed well, put in tube pan or oblong dish and refrigerate overnight.
Ready to slice and serve.

title: corn dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place baking dish in oven with margarine, onion and green pepper.
Melt margarine and cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove from oven and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: ladyfinger cheese cake
directions: Make both packets of Dream Whip and chill.
Drain pineapple. Line 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.

title: jewish apple cookies
directions: In small bowl, Combine all ingredients.
Stir and let sit.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water for 20 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup cold water.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar, vegetable oil, grated zucchini, flour, cinnamon, vanilla, baking soda and baking powder until all is well blended.
Add nuts; stir to blend.
Pour batter into greased and flour dusted pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in one layer in an oblong 3-quart baking dish.
In medium bowl, whisk together the undiluted soup and dry onion soup.
Gradually add sour cream.
Spread over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes, or until topping is lightly browned.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt together; then add corn and milk. Sift together baking powder and flour.
Add to liquids.
Mix lightly and drop by spoonfuls into deep-fat until brown.
Serve hot.

title: cinnamon oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Add sugar to eggs; mix well.
Add butter, stirring until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, mixing until blended after each addition.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Let batter stand 5 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are browned.
Cool on racks.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, apple butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Chill.
Serve with apples.

title: pot roast
directions: Heavily coat roast in flour.
Heat corn oil in frypan and brown all sides of roast to seal meat.
Place browned roast in roasting pan, add water, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cover and place in 375° oven for 2 hours (if gravy is too thin, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch in water and pour in roasting pan, cook additional 15 minutes).

title: bobby boom's breakfast burritos
directions: Scramble enough eggs for number you are feeding; set aside. Lightly coat fry pan with butter; heat burrito until slightly brown.
Place on plate; fill with scrambled eggs, onions, tomatoes, cheese and salsa.
Roll like eggrolls with ends closed. Place in microwave 1 minute to melt cheese.
Serve with grits.

title: valentine punch
directions: Combine and serve.
If desired, make "stirrers" by alternating red and green cherries with pineapple chunks on wooden sticks. Makes about 20 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place hamburger in bottom of pan.
Add other ingredients evenly over hamburger.
Place Tater Tots (frozen) on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn and corn muffin mix in a bowl; mix well.
Add egg and sugar; mix well.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Dot with butter.
Bake until top is brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender, drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in pan and drain.
Chop onions and add to beef.
In large saucepan, heat up all canned ingredients.
(Use soups undiluted.)
Mix everything together, except chips and cheese.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: hearts and flowers cake
directions: Combine
sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Beat on high speed for
minutes.
Sift
flour,
salt
and baking powder together. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to butter mixture, beating on low speed until smooth.

title: lee's favorite meaty manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown meat, onion and garlic together in skillet. Spoon off excess fat. Stir in salt, oregano, bread, parsley and 1/4 cup each spaghetti sauce and grated cheese. Cool slightly. Mix in Mozzarella, cheese and egg. Fill hot manicotti with stuffing. Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 12 x 7 ovenproof dish. Arrange manicotti in dish. Pour remaining sauce over the center third of the manicotti. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup grated cheese over top and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more. Serves 4.

title: applewood julep
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with ice cubes; mix well.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Makes 6 1/4 cups.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in a large saucepan. Slowly stir in water and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice, butter and apples.

title: pasta seafood gumbo
directions: Saute green onions and then add mushrooms.
While sauteing green onions and mushrooms; cook seashells according to directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: macaroni casserole italiano
directions: In a large skillet, crumble meat.
Cook until almost done. Drain.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add water, tomato paste, sauce mix and salt.
Stir until blended. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place meat between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound out to 8 or 9 inch diameter with mallet, very thin but no holes.
Place 1 slice ham and cheese on bottom half, fold over other half.
Press edges to seal.
Cover with wrap.
Pound lightly.
Sprinkle cornstarch on wrap. Lightly coat meat on both sides.
Over high heat, melt butter.
Add chicken pieces.
Cook 3 minutes on each side until meat is tender and golden.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: dad's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and baking soda; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Form dough into 4 rolls.
Roll in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Slice and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, clams, celery, onion and salt.
Add water and cover. Simmer 10 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan. Remove from heat and mix in flour until completely blended. Add milk and heat until thickened. Add vegetables, liquid and spices. Heat, being careful not to boil.

title: scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and baking powder.
Add Sultanas, egg and a little milk.
Mix.
Roll out on floured board 1-inch thick.
Cut out "biscuit style".
Brush tops with milk.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo (and oil if used) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oleo with other ingredients and return to pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bleu cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and shake well.
Makes 12 servings.

title: grilled bacon wrapped wieners
directions: Split wieners lengthwise part way.
Cut cheese in long strips and put one piece in each wiener.
Press together and wrap with bacon or ham, fastening the ends with toothpicks.
Roast on grill over hot coals until bacon is crisp and wieners are heated through. Yield:
8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter. Add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternately add flour mixture and milk, beating until blended after each addition.
Wrap dough in foil or plastic wrap and chill several hours or overnight.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Combine garlic, seasoned salt, cumin, chili powder, crushed red pepper, vegetable oil, lemon juice and cornstarch.
Add beef and marinate for 2 hours.
Chop onion and peppers.
Stir-fry beef until thoroughly cooked; remove from pan.
Stir-fry peppers and onions.
Re-add beef to heat up.
Place tortilla on plate; cover with damp paper towel.
Microwave for 30 to 45 seconds.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: moon rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls 1-inch size.
Roll in remainder of coconut.
Makes about 96 balls.
Chill until firm.

title: bacon-swiss tossed salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper. Layer salad.
Repeat layers twice. Cover and refrigerate.

title: jellied waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice and chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill several hours until firm.

title: spinach stuffing
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add cheese, chopped onion and butter to spinach and stir until all melted.
Turn into medium bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with dots of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bread pudding(microwave)
directions: Spread bread cubes in 8-inch round deep pie dish.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar, nutmeg, salt and then raisins.
Measure milk in 1-quart measure cup.
Add butter.
Microwave at High (10) for 4 minutes, melting butter and milk is warm.
Rapidly stir in eggs with fork; mix well.
Pour over bread cubes in pie dish. Microwave on Medium-high (7) for 9 to 12 minutes.
Center may be slightly soft, but it will set up as pudding cools.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit drops
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Dredge fruit with 2 tablespoons of this mix.
Mix remaining ingredients together, adding the fruit and nuts last.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place all ingredients except sesame seed into pot. Cover and simmer 45 minutes until tender, syrupy and brown.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top before serving.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Line pan with dried beef.
Wrap boned breasts in bacon.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over top.
Cover with foil, and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.
If you do double or triple recipe, be sure to have a large pan, the sauce seems to triple and run over.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Place granulated sugar in small, heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat without stirring until sugar melts and becomes golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add water slowly.
Cook without stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add milk.
Heat to almost boiling.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add flour, brown sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs and milk mixture. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened. Cover and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into baked shell.
Chill for several hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Roll biscuits in butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake, using temperature on biscuit can.
Remove while biscuits are still slightly doughy.
Do not overbake.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix sugar, melted oleo and milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix by hand real good.
Spread in greased pan. Keep in refrigerator 2 hours or freeze about 45 minutes.
Cut in small bars.
Melt dipping chocolate with enough paraffin to thin in top of double boiler.
Dip each bar.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: under the red sea - jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve lemon jello with water. Add marshmallows.
Whip the cream cheese. Add jello and marshmallows slowly while beating.
Add pineapple.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello together and let set in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Then take a portion of the jello and put in blender with oranges, cranberries and sugar.
Blend well.
Put all of mixture in bowl and add nuts.
Let set.
Stir every hour to keep fruit from settling on the bottom.

title: chicken napoli (lemon-butter chicken)
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish, pour mixture over chicken. Cook covered 45 min. on 350°. Uncover spoon mixture over chicken then cook 10-15 min. to thicken sauce. This is great cooked on the grill also.

title: tea punch
directions: Mix preceding and pour over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: sherried seafood
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; saute onion until tender.
Add mushrooms; saute about 2 minutes longer.
Add flour and salt; stir with wooden spoon until mixture has bubbled, about 1 minute. Slowly add milk, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Simmer until thickened.
Add shrimp, crab meat, pimento and sherry.
Serve over rice, toast points or patty shells.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Pound veal between plastic wrap.
Saute garlic and veal; set aside.
Saute peppers and add to veal and garlic.
Add tomatoes, dash of oregano, parsley and basil.
Cook on low flame 1 hour, until tender.

title: southern pecan pie cappuccino squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan melt butter; stir in flour until smooth.
Add brown sugar and 2 eggs, slightly beaten; mix well.
Cook over medium-low heat 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Dissolve instant coffee in hot water; stir into filling.
Add bourbon, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Set aside.

title: buckhorn inn's famous peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Put in crust bottom.
Save a little for the top.

title: caesar salad
directions: Sprinkle bottom of a wooden bowl with salt and rub it with garlic.
Add mustard, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce and stir with a wooden spoon until salt dissolves.

title: best big-batch tomato sauce
directions: In large pot or Dutch oven (about 8-quart) over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onions, carrots, green peppers and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, partially cover Dutch oven and cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 9 pints.
Can be doctored to your taste for meat sauce, marinara, Swiss steak, lasagna, etc.
Can be frozen.

title: nut crescents
directions: Have butter and cream cheese at room temperature.
Cream butter, cream cheese and egg yolk together.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour. Mix together thoroughly.
Shape into 4 logs and refrigerate several hours.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan.
Set aside.
In small bowl, with rotary beater, beat egg, sugars, mustard and paprika.
Add vinegar and beat again.
Blend into cooled butter or margarine.
Cook, stirring over low heat, just until thickened, 4 or 5 minutes.
Cool.
Good with cold ham or pork.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and the salt in a stone crock or bowl; mix well.
Add the water; beat to a smooth batter.
Add the vinegar.
Leave, covered with cloth, in warm place until sour (about 12 hours).

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up all fresh fruit.
Rinse strawberries and grapes. Combine cottage cheese with cinnamon and raspberry yogurt drink. Blend in sliced strawberries.
Arrange fruit on lettuce lined plates.
Place 4 ounces cottage cheese mixture in center of each plate for festive, nutritious lunch.
Serves 4.

title: royal marble cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in top of double boiler over hot water. Combine 3/4 cup flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Stir in 2 tablespoons chocolate.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen kolacky
directions: Combine flour and shortening. Mix as for pie crust.
Add yeast softened in a little warm milk and 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Add eggs, milk, sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Beat well.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Place on greased baking sheet. Brush with melted butter. Cover and let rise until almost doubled.
Make deep depression in center and fill with desired filling. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend together sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 2-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake 65 to 75 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: apple cornbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well, add eggs until blended.
Stir in corn meal alternately with milk.
Add apples.
Pour into an 8 x 10 inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: gooey cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
Punch holes in hot cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake; spread evenly, then add ice cream topping.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip over cooled cake. Crush frozen candy bars and sprinkle on top of cake.
Keep chilled.
Very good.

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Spoon filling evenly down center of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with cinnamon.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bring butter, sugars and apple juice to a boil in saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Pour over enchiladas.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add oil, milk and egg.
Stir with fork until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (too large puffs will not cook through) into deep hot oil at 375°.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll puffs in cinnamon-sugar or glaze by dipping into a thin confectioners sugar icing.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: diabetic thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix butter and liquid fructose thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt and add to mixture.
Combine well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; quickly press thumb gently on top of each cookie and spoon sugar-free fruit spread into impression.
Bake for 8 minutes longer.
Cool in refrigerator until jelly sets up.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Add the dates and cook this mixture until it gets thick. Add the nuts and pour it into a buttered dish.
Slice when it's cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil ingredients for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Cool. Place sliced berries in 2 cooked pie shells.
Pour mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip prior to serving.

title: fire and ice
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cook one minute and cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Pour hot milk in which 3 tablespoons butter is melted, over stuffing mix.
Mix squash, onion and seasonings. Fold in beaten eggs and herbed stuffing mixture. Turn into a 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with dry herbed stuffing; dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot-pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 80 four ounce servings.

title: tuna luncheon salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and add dressing to moisten. Chill well.

title: "grandpa boyd's" chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Beat cocoa with flour mixture while still hot.
Add buttermilk, soda, beaten eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: chocolate tornado
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Make a depression in the center; spread topping up sides of dishes.

title: au gratin fish supreme
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add mushrooms and onion and saute until onion is translucent. Sprinkle vegetables with flour, salt and pepper and stir quickly to combine; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Continuing to stir, gradually add milk and bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until mixture is smooth and thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in green beans and fish and cook until fish is heated through.
Set each muffin half on a flameproof plate; top each half with half of fish mixture and 1 ounce cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, about 1 minute.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into pieces.
Cut slices of onions and place over ribs.
Mix all ingredients listed and pour over ribs.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°, then lower to 350° until nearly done.
If you have covered them, remove cover and brown.
I often use foil over the pan for about an hour, then remove.
I use this for barbecuing pork chops also.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: In large saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar is completely dissolved. Continue boiling
rapidly
for
minutes.
Add cranberries; return to boiling.
Cook,
uncovered,
over
high heat 5 to 6 minutes or until skins pop off the berries.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: ellie's cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat this mixture until light with hand mixer.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Add salt to flour, then gradually add flour mixture to wet mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form 1/2-inch balls; dip first into slightly beaten egg whites, then into nuts.
Bake for 5 minutes; remove from oven.
Press with small glass to flatten and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: daddy's key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Blend in lime juice, then milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
If desired green food coloring may be used.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell (either graham cracker crust or pastry crust).
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until glossy peaks form.
Spread egg whites over surface of pie to edge of crust.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown (about 20 minutes). Chill before serving.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Pour in pan. Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Put sliced apples in cake batter in circle or straight lines, depending on shape of cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Hull berries and set aside.
Combine pie filling mix, sour cream, milk, rind and 2 cups of the Cool Whip in bowl.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Spoon half of the filling into the crust.
Arrange berries, stem down, in filling and press down.
Top with remaining filling.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: polish kluskis
directions: Brown bacon.
Add shredded cabbage and onions to grease; saute until tender.
Cook egg noodles in boiling water and then add to mixture.
Stir in cottage cheese and season with lots of pepper and a little salt.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 individual casseroles with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
In a small bowl combine Ricotta, egg, Mozzarella cheese, 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese and seasoning, mixing well.
Place cooked lasagna on a damp towel and spoon 1/4 of cheese mixture, lengthwise, along the center, starting from narrow end.
Carefully roll each noodle to enclose filling.
Place 2 rolls in each sprayed casserole and spoon 2 tablespoons sauce over each roll.
Sprinkle each roll with 3/4 teaspoon of Parmesan cheese and bake until thoroughly heated, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shimmering lemon marmalade
directions: If dieter's want to give themselves something special and not get off the calories wagon, they might try the low-to moderate calorie fruits or berries with small scoop ( 1/4 cup) of regular ice cream.
Choices include a 1/4 wedge of 5-inch cantaloupe (30 calories), 1/2 fresh pear, cored (50 calories), 1 cup fresh strawberries (50 calories) or 1 cup diced fresh pineapple (75 calories).

title: tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetable ingredients fine and cook together for one hour. Add sugar, vinegar, and spices. Cook for 45 minutes longer.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in skillet until lightly browned.
Stir in ketchup and remaining ingredients.
Add chicken and simmer, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and sauce is desired consistency.

title: seafoam
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Beat the egg whites and slowly pour the heated mixture over the eggs.
Add the vanilla flavoring and beat until firm.
Then drop on waxed paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat with salt and pepper.
Brown sugar and onions; drain.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add soups.
Layer meat and noodle mixture in casserole dish with cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Mix thoroughly lime gelatin and boiling water.
Add pineapple and place in refrigerator to congeal.
Mix lemon gelatin with boiling water.
Put into refrigerator to congeal.
When both mixtures are firm, whip the cream until stiff.
Take package of cream cheese and mix with lemon gelatin with mixer.
Fold whipped cream into lemon Jell-O-cream cheese mixture.
Pour on top of lime Jell-O.
Cover and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine.
Add crawfish and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes. Add soup and corn and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add 2 cups cooked rice (a little more may be added if desired) and parsley.
If you like seafood hot or spicy, add more seasoning to taste.
Put into greased casserole; cover with bread crumbs and bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until center begins to bubble.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Fold the vegetable mixture into the mayonnaise mixture.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put half of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate goober bars
directions: Grease bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Add milk and egg.
Stir until well blended.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Press nuts into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken rice
directions: Use oil to fry chicekn breasts.
Remove from oil; add water. Add cream of chicken soup until it boils.
Pour in 2 cups of rice; place chicken on top.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients well except pecans and add them last, then pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or more.

title: veggie canope
directions: Spread dough out on large bread pan. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients with electric mixer until blended into a thick cream.
Spread on top of cooled bread. Combine all vegetables and sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Take Saran Wrap and use to press cheese and vegetables down into mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecue pork ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Liquid Smoke may be added.

title: squash casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade caramel sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter, stir in sugar, syrup and water. Bring to a boil and stir in milk.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until it reaches the thread stage (230°).
Add vanilla and stir. Pour in jars or servers.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: orange rice stuffing
directions: In large saucepan, bring water and salt to boiling.
Gradually stir in rice.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes, or until rice is tender.

title: chili-potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cook and stir ground beef, green peppers, onion and salt in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, chili powder, water and beans.
Add to potatoes.
Cook for about 40 minutes (until potatoes are tender).
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Form into 4 small loaves.
Place in hot electric skillet with small amount of oil. Brown on one side then turn patties over.
Cook till brown.
Drain excess grease off.
Now place shredded potatoes over meat loaf patties.
Put 1/2 cup water over meat and potatoes.
Cook or steam till meat loaf and potatoes are done.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Heat until onions are tender.
Pour soup into soup cups and float a slice of bread on each. Place 1/4 cup cheese on top of bread.
Microwave 45 to 60 seconds to melt cheese.

title: peachy leg quarters
directions: Cut backbone from legs and reserve for broth.
Arrange legs in baking dish.
Brown in 450° oven.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Place 1 onion slice on top of each chop.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour over the pork chops and onion slices in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine and chill.
Top with 1/2 cup toasted slivered almonds or oriental noodles or both at serving time.

title: cheese krisps
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Mix well.
Mix flour with salt and red pepper.
Add to butter and cheese mixture. Mix thoroughly, then fold in Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°
for 20 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; add molasses and milk to suet. Pour into buttered mold and cover.
Steam 3 hours.
Serve with sauce.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Combine milk and butter in a small saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cool to lukewarm; add to flour mixture and beat until blended.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Stir in eggs, cheese and remaining flour.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; divide into two loaves and place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove loaves from pans at once and cool on wire racks.

title: cheese magic
directions: Put in food processor until soft.
Serve with Triscuit or Stoned Wheat crackers.

title: mousse with pineapple and candied peel
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve packing syrup.
