Cut each pineapple ring into 16 wedges.
Measure 1/2 cup of the packing syrup, add sugar, bring to a boil.
When sugar has dissolved, add pineapple wedges and boil for 5 minutes or until pineapple is a light caramel color.
Drain, put pineapple in a bowl with the Kirsch, return drained syrup to the pan.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Peel chicken from bones.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put broccoli on bottom.
Put chicken over the broccoli.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, milk and cheese; pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put cheese and chips on for 5 minutes; finish baking (35 minutes total).

title: sugar-free fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat bananas, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and butter until very creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Press with fork 1 way, then opposite way to get checker pattern.
Wet fork if necessary.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: baked beans and franks
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Combine mixture with other ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Advanced Prep:
In medium bowl, combine cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
In small bowl, stir together sour cream and sifted confectioners sugar.
Add to fruit mixture, mixing well. Line a 3-cup refrigerator tray with foil; pour in fruit mixture. Freeze firm.

title: bird nest clusters
directions: Put chips and peanut butter in a microwave-proof bowl. Microwave for 1 minute.
Remove, stir and put back in oven for 90 seconds or until melted.
Add chow mein noodles and mix until thoroughly coated.
Cover cookie sheets with wax paper.
Place golf ball size clusters of mix on paper to cool.
Flatten inside slightly to resemble a nest.
Add a couple of colored candies to each nest.
Can chill in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time. Mix thoroughly and add sifted flour, soda, salt, baking powder and mix. Add bananas and nuts. Pour into well greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45-60 min. Remove from oven and let stand in pan 10 min. Remove from pan, cool and slice.

title: cheese and sour cream casserole
directions: Brown beef; pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine onions with cream cheese and sour cream. Grease baking dish.
Layer noodles, sour cream mixture and meat sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat. Add onion and cook until transparent.
Drain all, but 2 tablespoons, of drippings.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat until it bubbles and turns golden brown.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings and cook, stirring, until thickened.
To serve, spoon over hot biscuits.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Crust:
Mix together crushed vanilla wafers and melted butter. Pat on bottom of 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan.
Arrange whole vanilla wafers around sides of pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and quarter sweet potatoes into heavy iron skillet.
Add sugar, salt, butter and water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased baking dish. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: classic sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well until smooth.
pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until fully settled.

title: ono chicken pineapple
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and place in small paper bag. Shake each chicken breast in bag; brown well in small amount of oil.
Drain any oil from pan.
Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce and sugar together.
Pour over chicken; cover and simmer until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
To serve, garnish with crushed pineapple.

title: grandma's red cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the cocoa and
food coloring. Add to the creamed mixture with the flour, salt, buttermilk, then flavoring.
Dissolve soda in vinegar and fold into mixture.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine bread, milk and water. Stir in eggs; blend well. Stir in pineapple and next 4 ingredients. Stir in butter. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until light brown.
Mix together the cream cheese, salad dressing and Ranch dressing powder.
Add milk, if needed.
Spread cheese mixture on cooled rolls.
Sprinkle on finely cut broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green pepper, mushrooms, celery and onion. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Any extra vegetables can be used according to your taste.
Cut into small squares for appetizer and large squares for lunch.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut up squash.
Boil until tender (or cook in microwave). Drain and mash.
Add all ingredients except half of butter.
Melt that and pour over mixture and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake a 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chicken las vegas(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Roll chicken in ham. Wrap 1 slice bacon around ham. Mix soup, water and salt. Put rice in casserole; layer chicken in rice. Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
(Optional, roll in crushed pecans.)
Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown ground meat; add vegetables and cook until tender.
Put all liquid items in bowl together.
When meat mixture is ready, add sauce mixture.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: You will need one large size (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic powder; saute.
Boil chicken until tender; skin and debone.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Break chicken into bite size pieces.
Place chicken, then broccoli, into rectangular baking pan.
Blend soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice; pour over chicken and broccoli and blend.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven. Top with shredded cheese.
Let stand about 15 minutes.
Serve as main dish or over rice.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and saute onion and garlic in it.
Add sour cream, soup and milk.
Mix well.
Shred chicken. Mix with salsa and chilies.
Shred cheeses together.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 cheese, 3 tortillas, 1/3 chicken mixture and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat until used up, using cheese last.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly and browned.
Top with olives.
Yields 8 servings.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat milk, oil and egg, then add to dry ingredients.
Fold in apples.
Cook as you would pancakes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze.
To serve as a slush, take out of freezer 3 hours before serving.
Can be served over crushed ice.

title: osgood pie(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, eggs and butter.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Then pour over crust.
Cut up bananas over mixture.
Add pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Mix with creamed corn.
Crush crackers and stir in melted butter.
Add 1/2 cracker mixture to broccoli and corn.
Pout in baking dish.
Put rest of cracker mixture on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with crushed pineapple.
Let set awhile. Add Cool Whip and mix.
Put in pan or bowl and top with marshmallows.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook until thick and clear; pour cooked juice over fruit hot. Make salad night before and refrigerate.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Fry refried beans in a skillet with bacon grease or cooking oil; season with garlic powder, onion powder and cumin to taste. Layer beans in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: south of border flip
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer a few minutes.
Spread meat sauce in pan, then layer drained beans, cheese and corn.
Prepare corn bread and spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Top each serving with lettuce, tomato, onion, sour cream and hot sauce.

title: scram spam pizza(in honor of stallion, "charmer boy")
directions: Combine hot roll mix with warm water according to package directions for pizza.
Press dough over greased 13-inch pizza pan, forming a rim around the edge.
Stir oregano, basil and garlic powder into the tomato sauce; spread over the dough.
Top with Spam, green pepper and cheeses.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until edges brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound flour and seasonings into meat with mallet.
Brown on both sides in bacon fat.
Add onions and 1 green pepper with bouillon.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender. Saute the 3 green peppers and tomatoes in butter for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with salt.
Place meat on warm platter. Stir Burgundy into meat drippings and heat.
Pour mixture over meat and top with peppers and tomatoes.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: great potato salad
directions: After cooking, peel potatoes and cube into small pieces while still warm.
If red potatoes, leave skin on.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients and pour over the warm potatoes.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, add the mayonnaise, onions and eggs.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook sausage (sliced), then saute with seasonings.
Mix in soup plus 2 cups water.
In another pot, cook macaroni and cheese according to directions, then mix both together in one pot and serve.

title: pork and bean or surprise bread
directions: In small bowl, pour boiling water over raisins and let stand. Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add oil, then pork and beans. Mix until beans are thoroughly mashed.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts if preferred.
Drain raisins and add to batter. Mix well.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter; stir in milk.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together well.
You should have a nearly stiff dough. Form the dough into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, until lightly golden.
Cool on racks and roll in powdered sugar.
May be stored in airtight container and also freezes quite well.

title: aunt dot's brown stew
directions: Brown meat in oil; add
enough water to cover after it's browned.
Cook about 1 hour, then add vegetables and cook until tender.
Brown 2 tablespoons flour
in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add 1 cup water.
Simmer for 2 minutes
on
low
heat.
Add
gravy to meat and vegetables.
Pour into
quart
casserole dish. Top with a can of biscuits.
Cook
at
until biscuits are done, about 15 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins and currants in 2 cups water.
Remove from heat. Cool and add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Sift together soda, salt, spices and flour.
Add fruit mixture and mix well. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Then add eggs, vanilla and banana flavoring.
Add bananas.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Chop celery, carrot, onion, garlic and jalapeno. In a skillet, saut in 1 teaspoon of cooking oil until seared and almost tender. Cut up chicken and add to the mixture. Simmer until chicken is cooked through but not very brown. Place mixture into a large pot. Add chicken broth, tomatoes with the juice, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.

title: spicy wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Barbecue or bake at 400° for about 40 minutes until done.

title: pork and bacon sausage
directions: Finely chop bacon in processor.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter and process sausage mixture until just blended, using on/off turns.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix chilled ingredients.
Pour into punch bowl with decorated ice mold.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with your favorite pie filling.

title: no bake drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk in saucepan.
Bring to full boil; boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Beat together.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: gouda burst
directions: Unwrap cheese; let stand at room temperature until softened. To form petals, make four 2 1/2-inch intersecting cuts in top of cheese ball.
Be sure to cut completely through plastic casing. Carefully pull back each section of casing, curling point around finger.
Scoop out cheese, leaving a 1/4-inch wall.
Refrigerate shell.
Mash cheese with fork.
Blend in milk, wine, mustard and red pepper sauce.
Fill shell with cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
One hour before serving, remove cheese in shell from refrigerator to soften.
Makes about 1 cup of dip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Soak rind overnight in lime and enough water to cover. Stir several times if possible. Second morning, drain off lime water and rinse rind in cold water 2 or 3 times. Cover with water and salt; bring to boil. Boil for 20 minutes and then drain. Make syrup of vinegar, sugar, cloves and cinnamon. Stir well; this is not heated. Add rind; bring to a boil. Boil for 10 minutes. Let stand overnight. Next a.m., boil again for 10 minutes. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken, reserving broth.
Melt oleo; add flour, making a dark brown roux.
Add onions, celery and okra.
Cook until slightly browned.
Add garlic, tomatoes, tomato paste, Accent, bell pepper, green onions and tops, parsley, oregano, thyme, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Add chicken broth (about 2 quarts).
Cook 1/2 hour or more.
Add chicken and simmer; serve over rice.

title: lisa's 4-h club pineapple cookies
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugars; cream.
Add beaten egg.
Add baking powder, salt and soda to flour.
Sift three sugar mixture.
Add drained pineapple.
Add vanilla.
Spoon onto cookie sheet; bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Allow all ingredients to reach room temperature.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Alternate adding flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix on high for several minutes until mixed well.
Scrape bowl and mix again.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Place in cold oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetables mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
(If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.)
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: greenback tomatoes
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Add remaining ingredients to spinach, except tomatoes, and cook over low heat until eggs are cooked.
Arrange tomatoes in a single layer in a buttered baking dish, 9 x 13.
Top with spinach mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chili powder.
Roll in chili powder.
Chill in refrigerator after wrapping in wax paper.

title: opossum pie
directions: Break or chip Ritz crackers (not too fine).
Do pecans the same.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in greased pie pan at 250° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Place in a baking dish.
Heat vegetables, chicken soup and milk; pour over beef and onion.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until Tater Tots are brown and crusty.

title: zucchini bread(with pudding)
directions: Grease pan extra well.
Mix all together.
Bake in 3 loaf pans.
Raisins and nuts may be added, if desired, or coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests with toothpick.

title: rice consomme
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° or 375° for 25 minutes.
Excellent served with roast.

title: tortellini basil soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add tortellini and cook 6 minutes or until tender.
Stir in beans and tomato.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in basil, vinegar and salt.
Ladle soup into individual bowls and sprinkle evenly with cheese and ground black pepper.
Yield:
7 cups (185 calories/cup).

title: swiss vegetable casserole
directions: Let vegetables thaw and drain well before mixing with the other ingredients.
Mix onions and grated cheese.
Set aside 1/2 of the onion and cheese mixture.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon the remaining onion and cheese mixture over the top of casserole.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with remaining ingredients, except almonds.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Turn on saucepan and add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Heat to boiling and add salt, pepper and celery seed.
Pour over one pound of shredded cabbage, one onion and one green (bell) pepper, chopped fine.
This will keep some time refrigerated.

title: peggy's almond delight
directions: Mix together margarine, brown sugar, coconut, almonds and flour.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch dish, stirring often to keep from burning.
Allow to cool.
Remove 1/3 for topping.
Mix in a bowl instant pudding and milk, beating until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Pour pudding mixture over baked mixture and sprinkle the 1/3 you have retained as a topping.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle small or large package of dry Jell-O over creamed cottage cheese; mix and then fold in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato into eight (8) wedges; arrange peel-side down, in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender.
Baste occasionally.
Makes eight servings.

title: chicken with mustard and wine sauce
directions: Cut up chicken into cubes; flour and brown in oil and butter. Drain chicken and set aside.
Mix mustard, wine and 2 tablespoons flour; shake well in small, covered container.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, covered. Serve over pasta.

title: mrs. virginia's blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 3 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in bowl of mixer with dough hook.
Mix 1 minute.
Combine milk, water and butter.
Heat 120° to 130° (approximately 2 minutes on High in microwave).
Turn to next speed and add liquid to flour mixture.
Mix about 30 seconds.
Mix 1 minute longer and add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough clings to hook and cleans sides of bowl, about 5 minutes.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes longer until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover, let rise 15 minutes.
Shape as desired.
Cover, let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: hot cheese and clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat in microwave for approximately 3 minutes or on low on stove, stirring after each minute.
Serve immediately with chips or crackers.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Layer 1 can of crescent rolls in bottom of lightly greased sheet cake pan. Mix 2 packages of cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, vanilla, and egg yolk together; spread on top of crescent rolls. Layer the second can of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture. Beat egg white with fork and brush over crescent rolls. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese
directions: Grind American cheese, garlic and pecans in food processor. Add room temperature cream cheese.
Make a roll on wax paper. Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap wax paper roll in aluminum roll and place in refrigerator.
Garlic cheese will slice better if made the day before you plan to serve.
Serve on Ritz or HiHo crackers.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add fruit cocktail and eggs; stir to blend.
Pour in pan and sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, rice, onion, green peppers, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well to blend.
Shape mixture in 24 meatballs about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Pour soup over meatballs.
Cover and slow cook, 7 to 8 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° to 375° until firm.

title: five bean bake
directions: Make the sauce by combining the tomato sauce, water, sugar, mustard and salt.
In a large pot, brown the sausage and onions. Add the celery and continue cooking until vegetables are clear. Add the sauce mixture.
Drain all of the beans.
(If you prefer a spicy taste, do not drain the chili beans.)
Add the beans and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour the mixture into a deep 9 x 13-inch pan. Fry, drain and dice the bacon; sprinkle over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tamale crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, tomato sauce, olives, catsup, onion and chili powder.
Simmer while preparing crust.
Separate dough in 8 triangles.
Place triangles in 8-inch or 9-inch square pan or deep 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Brush with oil and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon hot meat mixture in crust.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until golden brown.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Beat egg and milk and pour over noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour on top of spaghetti.
Add Ragu, mushrooms and olives.
Cover with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(May mix sauce with hamburger mixture.)

title: old fashioned beef soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat to a very slow simmer with just 2 or 3 bubbles coming up.
Simmer for 3 1/2 hours.
Add more water if soup simmered down too much.
Remove meat and bone.
Strain soup into another kettle.
Let come to a boil, then add noodles and cook slowly 10 minutes.

title: blender egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend at medium speed until mixed well.
Pour into heavily greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Crust forms on bottom.

title: baked ham and sweet potatoes
directions: Wash ham thoroughly.
Rub fat side with brown sugar and bread crumbs.
Dot with cloves.
Pare sweet potatoes.
Arrange potatoes around ham.
Pour crushed pineapple over ham.
Bake at 400°-425° for 3 hours.
Serves six.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese or crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: easy apples
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine together until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top with cinnamon and salt. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: microwave crunchy caramel corn
directions: Microwave Directions:
In large microwave-safe bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and nuts.
In 4-cup microwave-safe measuring cup, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds to 2 minutes or until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
(Mixture will become foamy.)
Pour over popcorn mixture and toss to coat.

title: hot tomato casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tortillas on 2 baking sheets in a single layer.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Turn tortillas and bake an additional 3 minutes.
Crumble and set aside.
While tortillas are baking, melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the flour and stir for 1 minute.
Do not brown.
Add chicken stock and nonfat milk.
Using a wire whisk, stir until it comes to a boil. Add salt, garlic powder and pepper and cook for 1 minute more. Add diced tomatoes to soup mixture, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: carrot oat muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk; let stand 15 minutes. Beat egg and honey. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir with egg mixture into oat mixture. Fold in carrots and orange rind, stirring only to moisten. Spoon into 12 muffin cups sprayed with nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 12.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, then oatmeal and milk. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture with raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sleepy time cocoa
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, mix sugar, water and cocoa.
Over low heat, stir until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Add milk to the saucepan; stir to mix the ingredients.
Over low heat, continue stirring until the cocoa is hot, about 3 minutes.
Remove the stove and turn the burner off.
Let cool 1 minute before testing.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add the beef; cook until brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place in casserole; top with potatoes (instant or regular).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are brown.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter `n' chocolate chip snack mix
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add Mandarin oranges, beat well.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes three 8-inch layers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool pans 10 minutes; remove and finish cooling. Frost and top with 1/2 cup pecans.

title: herbed chicken with vegetables
directions: Rub chicken (cut into serving pieces) with pepper and paprika. Place pieces in pan. Sprinkle on thyme and basil.
Add remaining ingredients to baking pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour peas into bottom of casserole dish.
Crumble about 8 to 10 saltine crackers over this.
Layer 1/2 the asparagus over this. Add about 8 to 10 more crackers.
Layer cheese over this.
Layer remaining asparagus.
Mix liquid from asparagus with soup.
Pour over asparagus.
Layer with more cheese and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Place chicken in the bottom of a shallow baking pan.
Combine your three cans of soup and wine and pour the mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
If deboning, cook for 30 minutes, covered, and then debone.
Pour sauce over and cook about 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Prepare pudding; blend in softened cream cheese until well blended.
Spread mixture on cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 25 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350°.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Melt Crisco on low fire.
Make white sauce by blending these ingredients:
Crisco, flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly and cook until thickens, stirring continuously.
Cool slightly.
Remove backbones from salmon and flake.
Beat egg and add to salmon along with onion powder, lemon juice and cracker crumbs.
Mix together in bowl.
Add white sauce and mix thoroughly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put layer of wafers, layer of bananas and layer of pudding. Repeat.

title: beef and pasta salad
directions: Combine beef, dressing and parsley, tossing to coat.
Cover bowl tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: 1015 casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with margarine or butter.
Thinly slice or dice (large pieces) onions.
Put a layer of crackers in dish.
Add a 1 to 2-inch layer of onions.
Sprinkle chicken bouillon granules.
Top with a layer of crumbled crackers.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over top.
Microwave until onions are tender.

title: herb garlic grilled chicken
directions: Combine parsley, garlic, lemon peel and mint.
Loosen skin from breast and thigh portion of chicken quarters by running fingers between skin and meat.
Rub some of the seasoning mixture over meat and under skin, then replace skin and rub remaining seasonings over outside of chicken.
Arrange medium-hot charcoal briquettes on one side of covered grill.
Place chicken on grill opposite coals.
Cover grill and cook chicken 45 to 55 minutes, turning once or twice.
Chicken is done when juices run clear. Serves 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole. Then add the following topping.

title: no cook banana or pineapple pudding
directions: Combine Cool Whip and sour cream (mix well with mixer). Pour in cold milk and pudding mix until thickens.
Add bananas or pineapple tidbits by hand.	Layer with wafers, then pour in pudding.
Crumble wafers on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash sweet potatoes; pat dry.
Brush a little oil on them.
Pierce a few times on each side.
Bake until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Once done, peel and mash, making sure there are no lumps remaining.

title: chocolate chip cookies(yields 4 dozen cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar, margarine and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add all remaining ingredients, except gumbo file and rice.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add gumbo file the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Serve over rice.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Layer first 4 ingredients and peas.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over salad, sealing edges.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps for several days.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter until tender.
Add broth and next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add half and half, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 quarts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Mix all ingredients and chill. Roll into 1-inch balls. Freeze on tray and store in container or freezer bag. When needed, thaw and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven or until lightly brown.

title: lemon coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place 1/2 cup of this mixture onto two crescent rolls still attached.
Fold over and press edges together.
Brush with soft margarine and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat can of soup and add 1 tablespoon pimento.
Pour over sandwiches before serving.

title: creamy taco
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Drain.
Add beans, cream of mushroom soup, tomatoes, taco seasoning mix and Velveeta cheese. Mix together.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve over chips or rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon and add to broccoli and cheese when cooled.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar separately.
Pour over other ingredients just prior to serving.

title: old fashioned cream pies
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in pie crust.
Gradually add cream and mix with fingers until no lumps are left.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cover green split peas with 2 quarts cold water.
Simmer gently 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Add ham bone, onion, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer (don't boil) 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone, just cut off meat and dice.
Return meat to soup and add celery and carrots.
Cook slowly uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake by regular cake directions.
Punch holes.
Pour strawberries, then Cool Whip.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix cookies and margarine together.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ice cream, then peanuts.
Freeze until solid. Spread hot fudge sauce on top; refreeze.

title: delicious hamburgers without buns
directions: Mold hamburger into 2 large patties and place on 2 large pieces of aluminum foil.
Put slices of onion, potatoes and strips of green pepper atop each patty.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Wrap securely in foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In glass 2-quart bowl, combine sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla; microwave on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds to 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda gently until light and foamy.
Pour at once on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 1/2 to 1 hour; break into pieces.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.
You may also heat in microwave oven on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil.
Mix until well blended (no mixer).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool cake.
When cool, frost with chocolate pudding.
When you serve, put on Cool Whip and a cherry.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spanish rice
directions: Boil first 9 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Add rice.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cover 5 minutes.
Flake with a fork.
Serve hot.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream.
Chop onion, tomatoes and olives.
In 3-quart casserole, layer bean dip, avocado dip, sour cream, onions, tomatoes, cheese and olives.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Beat yolks and gradually add brown sugar; beat well.
Add pumpkin, flour, salt, spice and cream and mix well.
Add hot milk and keep stirring until well mixed.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and slightly beat in; do not overbeat.
Pour in deep pie shell having liquid and whites in each pie.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then 350° until middle is set. Do not overbake.

title: quick apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and cut in quarters.
Separate rolls and wrap 1 piece of apple in each roll (start at large end).
Mix oleo, sugar and orange juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla. Place dumplings in 8-inch pan (square).
Pour sauce over apple dumplings and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy breakfast
directions: Mix ingredients together for a quick and healthy meal or snack.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Blend in milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In bowl combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: rough and ready cookies(an old, old recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix spices in flour. Add nuts and raisins last.
Raisins may be softened in warm water, then drained.
Use 3 tablespoons of this water to dissolve the soda.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Cook with onions in olive oil in large skillet until brown.
Drain.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir mushrooms and liquid into meat and onions.
Heat to boiling; cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat mixture into baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Arrange potatoes over meat.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream together margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar. Blend in crushed pretzels to make a crumbly mixture.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: vegetables three
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Worcestershire and grated onion. Refrigerate 2 hours ahead of serving time.
Cook lima beans. Drain.
Add green beans and peas with 1/2 stick butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until hot.
Heat sauce and pour over vegetables.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.
Easy and delicious.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolk, mix.
Add flour sifted with cinnamon.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Pour unbeaten egg white over surface - drain excess.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans, pressing lightly with hand.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while hot.
May be made ahead of time - freezes well.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add chicken broth.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: special vegetable pot roast
directions: Heat salad oil in Dutch oven or heavy kettle with a tight fitting lid.
Brown the beef quickly on all sides and sprinkle with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Chop all vegetables in small pieces (not through grinder, please).
Add the chopped vegetables to meat and cook over very low heat with tight cover for 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender when pierced with a fork.
Serves 6. Good with unthickened vegetable meat gravy over it.
Also, good cold.

title: grandma turner's veggie soup
directions: Cook beef in water until done, then add remaining ingredients. You can add a little more or less of the veggies you like or dislike.
Salt and pepper to taste or about 1/2 teaspoon of each. Once the meat is cooked you can add the veggies and then simply fill the cooker with water just over the veggies.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for at least 15 to 20 minutes.
Make a cooker full! Is great warmed over and is low in fat.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; simmer gently a few minutes to blend flavors.
Brush onto grilling meat.
Works well with beef, chicken or pork.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Melt sugar, water, oleo and flour in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Fill each pie crust with the sugared berries.
Fold pie crust in half and press edges to seal.
Put berry-filled crusts in pan with melted mixture.
Spoon mixture over crusts to coat them. Drop extra berries around sides of pan.
Cook in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: magic french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add sweetened condensed milk, salt, vanilla and nut meat.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into wax paper-lined pan and spread mixture evenly.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Turn out on a cutting board, with a sharp knife, cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch pieces.
In a paper bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add meat, a few pieces at a time.
Close bag and shake to coat.
Repeat with remaining meat.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup with the mixture and remaining half when adding the tuna mixture and noodles.
Next, add the soup, noodles and tuna mixture together in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and top with Cheddar cheese and sliced olives. Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
When cool, add Espresso coffee and vodka.
Chop dry vanilla bean in pieces and divide between bottles.
Pour liquid in bottles and shake every day for 3 weeks.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Best when made 24 hours before serving so flavors will blend.
Serve with Fritos scoops.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend everything together, except the whipping cream, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add whipping cream last on low speed until blended. Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 small bottles.
Stays fresh for 3 weeks.

title: hot 'n spicy shrimp dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice artichoke hearts.
Add shrimp, cream cheese, mayonnaise, picante sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 20 minutes or until heated through or microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Garnish with red pepper and green onions.
Serve with chips and assorted veggie dippers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: In 1-quart batter bowl, blend mayonnaise, yogurt, curry powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, cream cheese, and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time alternating with flour and ending with flour.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in cold oven set at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add all ingredients to the noodles. Bake in a greased casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) at 350° for 40 minutes, covered, then 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp in white wine
directions: In a wok, melt butter in 1 tablespoon olive oil over high heat until hot, swirling to coat sides of pan.
Add shrimp and stir-fry until shrimp are pink and curled, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove to plate. In same wok, heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry until soft, 3 to 5 minutes. Add wine, chicken broth, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Boil over high heat until reduced by one-third, about 3 minutes.
Return shrimp to wok.
Cook, tossing, for 30 seconds to heat through.
Add parsley and serve with rice and lightly sauteed zucchini.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Make three holes in this mixture.
In first hole, add vinegar and vanilla.
In second hole, add oil.
In third hole, put cold water.
Mix with a slotted spoon until lumps are gone.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: big-batch bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in a large kettle with stock and ham bones. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir in carrots, onion and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine flour and cold water until smooth.
Gradually stir into soup.
Cook for 10 minutes.
If too thick, add more water.
Serves 100 or makes 6 1/4 gallons.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water and set aside for 20 minutes.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla, then mix with oats in batter.

title: curry chicken
directions: Saute chicken in 4 tablespoons of oil with onion and garlic. Sprinkle curry powder on chicken and add 4 cups water, salt, pepper and soy sauce; bring to a boil.
Add diced carrots and potatoes.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch to 1/2 cup water, then to chicken and thicken.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: kathy's coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease round layer pan or square pan. Blend all ingredients, beating vigorously 1/2 minute.
Spread in pan.

title: strawberry supreme pie
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip.
Add fruit; blend.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Place in fridge 45 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: zippy franks
directions: Melt jelly with the mustard.
Add the horseradish and franks that have been cut into 1-inch pieces.
Heat and serve.

title: beef scaloppine marsala
directions: On cutting board, pound each steak to 1/8 inch thickness with mallet or side of meat cleaver.
Cut steaks into about 4 x 2-inch pieces.
In pie plate, beat egg with milk.
On waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.

title: gouda in puff pastry
directions: Thaw pastry.
Peel Gouda and spread with mustard.
Wrap each cheese with a sheet of pastry.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into wedges and serve with fruit.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients and press in bottom of spring-form pan.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Roll crackers to crumbs and reserve 1/2 cup.
Cut marshmallows into small pieces with wet scissors.
Combine crumbs, marshmallow pieces, nuts and dates.
Add cream slowly until mixture is moist enough to hold together.

title: cream cheese mints(heritage recipe)
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft, add color and flavor. Gradually beat in powdered sugar.
Knead the mixture until of a pie dough consistency.
(A soft or firmer candy can be made by adding or decreasing sugar.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Line a medium-size dish (9 x 13-inch) with vanilla wafers. Beat together the margarine, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread creamed mixture over wafers.
Cover with a layer of berries.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Best to make and serve the same day.

title: grandma's peanut butter pie
directions: Crumble together the peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Then follow directions making pudding.
Put 1/2 of crumbled mixture on top of crust, then pour on vanilla pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with remaining peanut butter crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish (except crackers).
Sprinkle top with a few cracker crumbs and paprika, if you like.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: he-man cake
directions: Put first five ingredients in a cooker and bring to a boil. Let cool.
Mix cocoa mixture with last 7 ingredients.
Bake on a cookie sheet with edges.
Bake at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and press out as much excess moisture as possible.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
(Can be frozen at this point.)
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Put sugar, salt, soda and baking powder in a bowl and add buttermilk.
Stir well, then add corn meal and flour alternately. Melt shortening; add to mixture and pour into hot pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
